<h1>
<a name="RTFToC3">MINUTES OF MEETING </a></h1>
<p>
<b>November 3, 1994 :</b><p>
<h2> <a name="RTFToC4">I/ Presentation of on-going activity (see copies of slides in annex 1) : </a></h2>
<u>Presentation of Dr HAGEN work by Dr FEISTEL </u>:<p>
<p>
Work of Mauritania cruise of the Hudson and Humbolt. Cap GHIR very interesting
region. A lot of <i>in-situ</i> data available. All the data are available for
the network.<p>
<p>
<p>
 <u>Presentation of JRC-IRSA by Walter EIFLER</u> :<p>
<p>
Ongoing work on clouds, DMS,. Primary production, more information will come
for the yearly report. Interest in level "4" data.<p>
a) Working on ocean modelling - presentation of ISPRAMIX<p>
b) Data assimilation by the adjoint model method.<p>
<p>
Concrete and fruitfull collaboration with Rostock with the measurement for
assimilation.<p>
Carefull in using the wind field given by the Met. Office (it is a very strong
user requirement to have a good wind field).<p>
<p>
<p>
 <u>Presentation of Puertos del Estado work by Dr SANCHEZ-AREVALO </u><p>
<u>and Margarita ESTEBAN</u> :<p>
<p>
Model in the box 21W - 26 N and preliminary results presented.<p>
<p>
<p>
 <u>Presentation of ACRI on-going and planned work by Philippe BARDEY :</u><p>
<p>
<p>
 <u>Presentation of ARMINES</u> :<p>
<p>
GIS presentation by Mr KARAGEORGIS :<p>
- Georeference<p>
- Raster or vector<p>
- 3D parameter<p>
<p>
Mr WALD : 	Meteosat data + AVHRR data<p>
		4 value/day of energy Kwh/m[[twosuperior]] and monthly data August, Sept,
Oct, Nov. 92. 		same area and period as Rostock data could be used to derive
Par (O+).<p>
<p>
<p>
 <u>Presentation of Universit&auml;t of Hamburg by Angelo RUBINO :</u><p>
<u></u><p>
Transient gravity flow.<p>
<p>
A/ After the presentation a common definition of the area of interest has been
decided and is divided in 3 sub zone : <p>
<p>
<pre>
			(I)   18deg.N - 26deg.N	)
    Working area :	(II)  26deg.N - 30deg.N	)	20deg.W - 8deg.W
			(III) 30deg.N - 32deg.N.)
</pre>
<p>
<p>
B/ All bathymetric data for this zone wil be collected from different sources
and integrated in a uniform package for general purpose use.<p>
<p>
Universit&auml;t of Hamburg will obtain contour map at I' resolution. Maps will
be centralized at EMP to be processed in the GIS.<p>
<p>

<h2>
<a name="RTFToC5">II/
Contractual aspects :
</a></h2>
All position are filled except for Rostock. Two options are still pending :<p>
<p>
1- They will hire the candidate as post-doc if possible to solve administration
matter (see contract),<p>
2- The coordinator of the network will take care of the administrative matter
and make the candidate available for the network.<p>
<p>
Contract status. OK expert Rostock. They will take contact with the
Universit&auml;t of Hamburg to solve administrative matter.<p>
<p>
Individual Progress Reports will be integrated for the end of the year and
should include technical and financial justification.<p>
<p>
<p>
<b>November 4, 1994</b><p>
<b></b><p>
PECO on-going. (PECO proposal sent to HCM members).<p>
<p>
Available data base :<p>
<p>
1- Puertos del Estado - Data bank<p>
	- Ware buoys network. Scalar buoys + directional.<p>
	- Tidal gages (sonar tidal gages).<p>
<p>
Operative = 10 years.<p>
<p>
<p>
2-  Rostock data :<p>
<p>
- CTD, O² all profile : 0 - 500 m <p>
   32deg.N - 2000 m.<p>
- Radio sounding 5 to 10.<p>
- Satellite IRs at ISPRA.<p>
<p>
3- ISPRA - Check with Peter, see also HCM data base.<p>
<p>
4- ACRI Data base validated.<p>
<p>
5- EMP - Meteosat Data 	- Radiation map.<p>
					- Measurement of heat flux.<p>
<p>
6- Universit&auml;t of Hamburg - Precise context of data base.<p>
<p>
Map topographic send to EMP 	- Puertos del Estados : map of Spain.<p>
						- ACRI : SHOM<p>
						- University of Hamburg : German map.<p>
Vector shoreline.EMP will coordinate geographical data and proposed shoreline<p>
+ bathymetry fields.<p>
<p>
To all : <p>
Check and inform ACRI on :<p>
<p>
- Commercial available data.<p>
- CD Rom.<p>
- Software Package.<p>
<p>
<p>
 <u>Presentation of WWW by Mr GARNESSON</u>.<p>
<p>
Acknowledge Collaborating Institutes 	ex : University of Athens<p>
							       LPCM<p>
							       NRL etc<p>
<p>
Next Meeting in MADRID to be held on April 6 and 7 1995.<p>
