<HTML>
<HEAD>
<TITLE>TIS Security Consulting for Government Programs and Agencies</title>
<!-- Copyright 1996 Trusted Information Systems -->
<!-- Design and programming: The James Gang (jgang@jamesgang.com) -->
</HEAD>

<body bgcolor="#FFFFFF" text="#000000" Link="#191970" VLink="#B22222" ALink="#B22222">

<center>
<a href="/docs/products/consulting/index.html">
<IMG width=230 height=33  SRC="/docs/images/tisc.gif" border=0 ALT="TIS Consulting"></A>
<HR  size=2 >
<IMG width=172 height=16 SRC="/docs/images/govtcon.gif" border=0 ALT="Government Consulting">
</center>

<HR  size=2 >

<!-- Main Body -->

<Font size= 6>TIS Security Consulting for Government Programs and Agencies</font>
<BR>
<Blockquote>
Trusted Information Systems, Inc. possesses the in-depth knowledge of and extensive
experience in the specialized security requirements of government programs.   TIS' solid
security technology base has enabled us to devise system security designs, modeling
and assessment support for major systems development.  TIS security
analysts and trust engineers prepare a thorough system review that identifies the threats,
vulnerabilities, and risks associated with information systems in
operational and developmental environments, and provide models of proposed architectures and
recommendations for system improvements.<P>

<H3><A HREF="engineer.html"><IMG SRC="/docs/images/tengineer.gif" border=0 align=middle ALT="Trust">
Trust Engineering</H3></a>

TIS has over 13 years of experience developing and
evaluating trusted systems based on national and international security criteria.<P>

<H3><A HREF="certif.html"><IMG SRC="/docs/images/certif2.gif" border=0 align=middle ALT="Certification">
Certification and Accreditation</h3></a>
<P>
TIS personnel have supported many government agencies and system integrators
concerned with deploying INFOSEC.
<P>
<H3><A HREF="govcon.html"><img src="/docs/images/flags2.gif" border=0 align=middle ALT="Govt Consulting">
TIS Government Consulting Activities</H3></a><P>
Descriptions of some of the most recent projects and activities in which TIS particpates.<P>

</BLOCKQUOTE>
