<!--top-->

<FONT SIZE=6>Data Security Letter</FONT><FONT SIZE=2>&reg;</FONT>

<BLOCKQUOTE>

We would like to take this opportunity to introduce our colleagues
in the information systems security community to the<I><B>Data Security Letter.</B></I> Published eleven times a year, the <I><B>Data Security Letter</B></I>
focuses on computer and communications security with particular
emphasis on the latest research and technology news. Written by
leading computer security professionals, the <I><B>Data Security Letter</B></I> includes feature articles on contemporary topics, reference lists,
summaries of current research and development projects, highlights of
conferences and other professional events, and a wealth of other
subjects of interest to computer security and information systems
professionals.  Issues are 12 to 16 pages in length.<P>
 The <A HREF="/docs/products/dsl/dslindex.html">1995 Index of Articles</A>,
covering  January - December 1995 (#56 - #66), provides some insight
into the focus and concerns of the <I><B>Data Security Letter.</B></I>
This index gives an overview of the great range of topics
we address, from the most current Internet-related security concerns to
an array of ongoing government and industry initiatives.  
<P>
<blink><B><I>Special Offer:</I></B></blink> Receive a free evaluation copy of a recent issue of the Data Security Letter.  Send your name and postal address along with your request to: <A HREF="mailto:dsl-sample@tis.com"><I>dsl-sample@tis.com</I></A> .Or you may fax your request to (301) 854-5363,<I> Attention: DSL</I>; or you may telephone (301) 854-5338.

<HR> 

<B>Mission Statement:</B>The <I><B> Data Security Letter</B></I> provides data
security professionals with a depth and breadth of computer security
information, exploring fully topics touched on only superficially
elsewhere, with an emphasis on ongoing research, recent trends, and
their application to the needs of government and industry.<P>



<P>
<B>In Upcoming Issues:</B><P>

<UL>

<LI><B>Cryptography:</B> We provide continuing
and timely discussion of contemporary crypto topics, such as government
crypto policy (including key escrow and export controls), international
cryptography, and government and industry standards.<BR>

<LI><B>Internet:</B> The enormous growth of the Internet and the related security topics are given regular attention in the Data Security Letter (DSL).<BR>

<LI><B>Government initiatives</B> -- by the DoD, NIST, and other agencies -- receive
thorough, timely coverage.<BR>

<LI><B> Ongoing conference &amp; event coverage
</B>is featured in the DSL.  We include 
write-ups on conferences such as Oakland, Franconia, and the National 
Information System Security (NISS) Conference sponsored by the NCSC and 
NIST, which are but a few of the major security events we cover.<BR> 

<LI><B> Regular features</B> such as the Calendar of Events, Research Activities of
Note, and People on the Move keep readers apprised of
current happenings.<BR> 

</UL>
<HR>


<B>Opening communications channels</B> with our readers is an important part of the<I><B>
Data Security Letter</B></I> publishing
philosophy.  We solicit and welcome reader input, especially for
such regular features as the Calendar of Events, People on
the Move and - one of our most timely features - Research
Activities of Note, where we feature research projects underway
at a variety of companies, government agencies, and universities.
 Whenever possible and with permission, we include E-mail addresses
and other information on points-of-contact for all of the topics
we cover.  We firmly believe that given all of the exciting new
developments underway in the information systems security community,
the sharing of experiences and information is more important now
than ever.<P>

<HR>

<I><B>Data Security Letter&reg;</B></I>
<P>

<B>Editorial Board: </B>Stephen T. Walker, Eliot Sohmer, and Steven B. Lipner<P>

<B>Editor:</B>  Sharon P. Osuna<P>

This newsletter is published eleven
times a year.  Institutional rate: $345/year (unlimited local
copying permitted); individual rate: $89/year (may not be reproduced
without prior written permission of Trusted Information Systems,
Inc.). Foreign airmail $25/year extra.  Maryland residents, please
add 5% state sales tax.  Visa/MasterCard accepted.<P>

<B>Mail address: </B>3060 Washington Road (Rt.97), Glenwood, MD  21738  USA<BR>
<B>Telephone: </B>  301-854-5338<BR>
