<HEAD><TITLE>Network Security</TITLE>
<!-- Copyright 1996 Trusted Information Systems -->
<!-- Design and programming: The James Gang (jgang@jamesgang.com) -->
</HEAD>

<body bgcolor="#FFFFFF" text="#000000" Link="#191970" VLink="#B22222" ALink="#B22222">

<center>
<a href="/docs/research/index.html">
<IMG width=216 height=28  SRC="/docs/images/tisr.gif" border=0 ALT="TIS Research"></A>
<HR  size=2 >
<a href="/docs/research/network/index.html">
<IMG width=112 height=15 SRC="/docs/images/nsecurity.gif" border=0 ALT="Network Security"></a>
</center>

<HR  size=2 >

<!-- Main Body -->

<Font size= 6>Network Security</font>
<BR>
<CENTER>
<IMG width=96 height=99 SRC="/docs/images/network.gif" border=0 ALT="Network Security">
</CENTER>
<BLOCKQUOTE>
TIS participates in network security standards activities to further the development, implementation, and deployment of network security standards for the Internet community. We are currrently working on the following projects.

	<UL>

<LI><B><a href="/docs/research/network/dmsfw.html">
Defense Message Service Firewall Plus</A></B><BR>
TIS/DMS Firewall Plus is a Fortezza-emabled X.400 mail guard/firewall. <P>

<LI><B><a href="/docs/research/network/iip.html">
IIP-Internet Infrastructure Protection</A></B><BR>
TIS is employing digital signature and other techniques to support data origin authentication and data integrity security services to protect against accidental failures and malicious attacks for certain chosen infrastructure protocols: domain name system and routing.

<p>
		<UL>
		<LI><B><a href="/docs/research/network/dns.html">
		Domain Name System Security(DNSSEC)</A></B><BR>
		A DARPA-sponsored project that provides a translation of host names to Internet addresses.
		<LI><B><a href="/docs/research/network/snmp-ng.html">
		Simple Network Management Protocol - Next Generation</A></B>
</UL><P>

<LI><B><a href="/docs/research/network/nsso.html">Network Security Standards and Operation</A></B><BR>
TIS participates in network security standards activities to further the development, implementation, and deployment of network security standards in the Internet community.
<P>

<LI><B><a href="/docs/research/network/moss.html">MOSS-INFOSEC for Networked Systems</A></B><BR>
TIS is encouraging the broad adoption of secure email technology in the Internet by enhancing and maintaining a base secure email technology.
<P>
<LI><B><a href="/docs/research/network/ovp.html">
Extended Secure Internet Access and Service</A></B><BR>
A project to extend functionality for the TIS Internet Firewall Toolkit (FWTK) 
		<P>
		<LI><B><a href="/docs/research/network/ult.html">
		User-Level Truffles</A></B><BR>
		User-Level Truffles is a DARPA/ITO-sponsored joint project between Trusted Information Systems, Incorporated (TIS) and the Computer Science Department of the University of California at Los Angeles (UCLA). TIS and UCLA intend to build on their experience with replicated file systems and public key infrastructures for privacy enhanced mail to develop a user-level, distributed, replicated file system, with security.
		<P>

</UL>

</Blockquote>

