<HEAD><TITLE>Crypto Solutions</TITLE>
<!-- Copyright 1996 Trusted Information Systems -->
<!-- Design and programming: The James Gang (jgang@jamesgang.com) -->
</HEAD>

<body bgcolor="#FFFFFF" text="#000000" Link="#191970" VLink="#B22222" ALink="#B22222">

<center>
<a href="/docs/research/index.html">
<IMG width=216 height=28  SRC="/docs/images/tisr.gif" border=0 ALT="TIS Research"></A>

<HR  size=2 >
<a href="/docs/research/crypto/index.html">
<IMG width=180 height=16 SRC="/docs/images/cryptographic.gif" border=0 ALT="cryptographic"></a>
</center>
<HR  size=2 >

<!-- Main Body -->

<Font size= 6> Cryptographic Technologies</font>
<BR>
<CENTER>
<IMG width=252 height=166 SRC="/docs/images/metalkey.gif" border=0 ALT="Crypto">
</CENTER>
<Blockquote>

<A HREF="/docs/research/crypto/survey/index.html">
<B>Crypto Products Survey</B></A> <BR>
TIS has conducted a comprehensive 
Crypto Products Survey which looks at the availability of 
cryptographic products throughout the entire world.
<P>
<A HREF="/docs/research/crypto/ice/index.html">
<B>International Cryptography Experiment (ICE)</B></A><BR>
The International Cryptography Experiment (ICE)
calls for a series of experiments to promote the international
use of cryptography in common computer software applications (i.e.,
word processors, spreadsheets, electronic mail systems) in a manner
that uses Cryptographic APIs to separate the application from the cryptography
and allow for individual national controls on the cryptography
without restricting the applications software.
<P>
<a href="/docs/research/crypto/ckrpolicy.html">
<B>Key Release Policy (KRP)</B></a><BR>
TIS is developing a Policy-Based Cryptographic Key Release Language that meets a broad set of requirements.
The language forming the foundation of the system provides a flexible vehicle
for users and organizations to describe/select an appropriate policy for
releasing the key that is protecting information under their control.
<P>

<B><A HREF="/docs/products/cke/index.html">RecoverKey (<i>formerly</i> CKE)</A></B> <BR>
The RecoverKey family of technologies gives users emergency encryption key recovery for their important information by securely hiding a "spare secret key" with the encrypted information.  RecoverKey International is configured to enable easy export of good encryption (e.g., 56-bit DES).

</BLOCKQUOTE>
