<BLOCKQUOTE>



<I>Trusted Information Systems, Inc. (Glenwood, Maryland)</I>

<H3>Positions Open at TIS - Headquarters</H3>
<hr>
<A NAME="DEMDES">
<H3></A>Demonstration Designer</H3><P>
       
Trusted Information Systems, Inc. has an immediate opening for a
Demonstration Designer in the Business Development/Marketing Department in
their Glenwood, MD office.  The position entails the creation of
user-friendly, interactive, portable, graphic demonstrations for on-going
research and product development projects.
<p>
The successful candidate must have a strong background in computer
animation, computer graphics, multimedia, CD-ROM production, and
communications.  The ideal candidate must be able to work well with a wide
variety of technical and marketing personnel to integrate technological
concepts into understandable reality.  This person must be flexible,
enthusiastic, and a self-starter with creative ideas.  Programming skills
and interest in computer/network security a plus.
<P>
For prompt consideration, please contact the Personnel Office.<p>
Send resume and letter to 
<A HREF="mailto:hrweb@tis.com">hrweb@tis.com</A>,
or FAX to 301-854-5363, ATTENTION: Human Resources.<P>

EEO/AA<hr>



<A NAME="GENLA">
<H3></A>General Ledger Accountant</H3><P>
                       
Trusted Information Systems, Inc. has an immediate opening in their
Glenwood, MD facility for a General Ledger Accountant.  The successful
candidate will prepare general ledger account reconciliations and assist in
the monthly and annual general ledger closings according to generally
accepted accounting principals and TIS's policies and procedures.  Other
responsibilities include preparation of schedules for annual audits; ad hoc
reporting and maintenance of fixed asset subsidiary ledger.
<P>
This position requires a Bachelor's degree in accounting with two to three
years accounting experience.  Proficiency in Excel is a must and experience
with Deltek a plus.
<P>
Send resume and letter to 
<A HREF="mailto:hrweb@tis.com">hrweb@tis.com</A>,
or FAX to 301-854-5363, ATTENTION: Human Resources.<P>

EEO/AA<hr>
<A NAME="TECH">
<H3></A> Compensation Specialist/Technical Recruiter</H3><P>

Trusted Information Systems, Inc., a world leader in computer/communications security, 
has an immediate full time position for a Manager of Technical Compensation with a 
background in Technical Recruiting, with the Human Resources Department in the 
Glenwood, MD office.  This person will provide the primary input to development, 
administration and maintenance of technical staff compensation structure, 
incorporating field market knowledge with design guidelines provided by the 
Vice President of Human Resources.  The successful candidate will also be 
responsible for identification, development, evaluation and recruitment of 
technical personnel for TIS.  This person will work with TIS management to 
identify and document open positions, develop candidate specifications, 
manage advertising and other recruiting efforts, receive resumes 
(electronically and otherwise), screen candidates, coordinate interview 
process, conduct reference checks, and support the offer process.   
<P>

The successful candidate must have a college degree, preferably in Human
Resources, with 5-7 years experience in HR with a heavy emphasis in compensation 
and recruiting.  The last two years of recruiting should be in a high tech 
software environment. 
<P>
Send resume and salary requirements to HR Dept., Trusted Information Systems, 
Inc., 3060 Washington Road (Rt. 97) Glenwood,MD 21738;  by email to  
<A HREF="mailto:hrweb@tis.com">hrweb@tis.com</A>,or FAX to 301- 854-5775. <P>
EEO/AA

