<P>
<Font Size=6>RecoverKey&#153; Group</FONT>
<P>


<I>Trusted Information Systems, Inc. (Glenwood, Maryland)</I>
<BLOCKQUOTE>

<H3>Positions Open in the <A HREF="/docs/products/cke/index.html">
RecoverKey</A> Group</H3>

<a NAME="crypto">
<H3></a>Crypto Products Marketing Manager</H3>

Trusted Information Systems, Inc., has an immediate opening for a full time
Crypto Products Marketing Manager. The successful candidate will further
develop marketing activities for its patented RecoverKey(tm) technology and
other cryptographic products. This position involves product management and
refinement of product plans through interaction with the Business
Development VP and the product development group. It also includes
coordination of promotional and presentation material and public relations
activities with an external firm.<P>

Requirements:  Five (5) years experience in hands-on high technology product
management and experience in marketing environments, preferably involving
licensing of intellectual property rights to partners, in addition to
dealing with mass market products.<P>

This position will report to Executive Vice President of Cryptographic
Products. The successful candidate must be a positive and enthusiastic
person with excellent communication, analytical, technical, organizational,
and interpersonal skills; must be a self starter who works well
independently with little supervision and is able to handle multiple tasks
simultaneously.<P>

Familiarity with generally accepted marketing materials development software
such as Microsoft Office and Adobe Persuasion, and layout and production
software such as Quark express and Adobe Photoshop are highly preferred.<P>

Some travel, possibly international, will be required. Compensation will
include a base salary plus an incentive bonus plan for achieving corporate
goals, and potential stock options.  <P>

TIS is a publically traded company on the NASDAQ exchange under the symbol TISX.<P>

For prompt consideration, please contact the Pesonnel Office.  Send resume,
letter and salary requirements to <a href="mailto:hrweb@tis.com">hrweb@tis.com</a>,
or FAX to 301-854-5775,
ATTENTION - Human Resources.<P>

EEO/AA<P>

<A NAME="SOFT">
<H3></A>Software Test/Manufacturing Engineer</H3><P>
Trusted Information Systems, Inc., has an immediate opening in their
Glenwood, MD facility, for a software test/manufacturing engineer to join
the team producing software encryption products, including RecoverKey&#153;.  The
work will involve the following aspects of system testing and manufacturing:<P>
<UL>
<LI> assisting with software system testing and quality assurance for
commercial software releases on UNIX and Windows (NT, 95) platforms
<LI> assembling and shipping products (software, hardware, documentation, and
other materials) to customers
<LI> coordinating the shipment of products via integrators, software test team,
and software configuration management
<LI> maintaining an inventory of documentation, software, hardware, and other
materials
<LI> maintaining a database related to product shipping
<LI> assisting with the preparation of user documentation
<LI> coordinating media replication and documentation with outside vendors
</UL>

Candidates for this position must possess a Bachelors degree in a related
field and at least two years of applicable experience.  Some experience in C
programming.  Knowledge of UNIX (BSD), MS Windows (NT,95), test
methodology, and software quality assurance. Ability to work well in a team
environment.  Must have good English language communication skills, both
verbal and written. Must have good analytical and interpersonal skills.
Must have an understanding of basic computer hardware configuration.  Must
be customer focused and oriented.  Relevant experience in software
development, security, cryptography, and hardware/software installation
desirable.<P>

For prompt consideration, please contact the Pesonnel Office.  Send resume,
letter and salary requirements to <a href="mailto:hrweb@tis.com">hrweb@tis.com</a>,
or FAX to 301-854-5775,
ATTENTION - Human Resources.<P>

EEO/AA<P>

</BLOCKQUOTE>

