<!-- Main Body -->
<P>
<Font Size=6>Network Security Jobs</FONT>

<BLOCKQUOTE>



<I>Trusted Information Systems, Inc. (Glenwood, Maryland)</I>

<H3>Positions Open in the <A HREF="/docs/research/network/index.html">
Network Security R&D</A> Group</H3><P>
<hr>

<A NAME="SWENGR">
<H3></A>Software Engineer</H3><P>

Trusted Information Systems, Inc. in Glenwood, Maryland is seeking
experienced software engineers to join our network security research
and development activities.  This group is involved in efforts
directed at applying cryptographic protections to Internet protocols.
Presently, the group is investigating enhancing the Internet
infrastructure protocols, especially the Domain Name System (DNS) and
routing protocols, to include digital signature services.  Engineers
would be responsible for designing and implementing security
enhancements and extensions for protocols in the TCP/IP suite.
Successful candidates will participate in identifying security
vulnerabilities in other network protocols and methods of providing
security enhancements.<P>

A qualified candidate must have at least two years of experience with
network protocols, either design, implementation, or testing, and at
least 2 years of software development experience with the C
programming language.  Experience with the TCP/IP protocol suite and
the use of cryptography in support of security services preferred.  A
bachelor's degree or coursework and additional experience is required.<P>

Send resume and letter to 
<A HREF="mailto:hrweb@tis.com">hrweb@tis.com</A>,
or FAX to 301-854-5363, ATTENTION: Human Resources.<P>

EEO/AA<P>

</BLOCKQUOTE>

