<P>


<I>Trusted Information Systems, Inc. (Glenwood, MD Office)</I>
<BLOCKQUOTE>
<H3>Positions Open in the 
<A HREF="/docs/research/operating/index.html">Operating Systems and Firewalls Research</A>
Group</H3>
<HR>
<H3><A NAME="UNIXDEV"></A>UNIX Developers</H3>

<P>
Trusted Information Systems, Inc. in Glenwood, Maryland is seeking
experienced software developers to participate in the conceptualization
and prototyping of new security mechanisms for operating systems and
networks.  Qualified candidates must have at least a bachelors degree
and 3 years experience programming UNIX systems or an advanced degree in
computer science.<P>

Skills in the following areas are desirable:  development of distributed
applications, object-oriented design techniques and CORBA; compiler
technologies; the TCP/IP protocol suite, particularly the Domain Name
System; Internet firewalls; UNIX internals; and UNIX system
administration.<P>

Successful candidates must have excellent analytical, communications,
and interpersonal skills; be able to deal with abstract ideas and
requirements; and function independently and productively in a research
environment with little supervision.<P>

Please send resume to 
<A HREF="mailto:hrweb@tis.com">hrweb@tis.com</A>
or by FAX to 301-854-5363, or by US
Mail to:  Trusted Information Systems, Inc., 3060 Washington Road,
(Rt.97), Glenwood, MD 21738.<P>

EEO/AA<hr>

<A NAME="TEAM">
<H3></A>Computer Security Research Team Leader</H3><P>
Trusted Information Systems' Glenwood Office has an opening for a full-time, 
experienced computer/network security professional to lead a research team 
developing innovative software security technologies.  Must have Bachelors 
of Science in related field, 5 years software development experience, 
security background, ability to generate new research ideas, write proposals 
and technical reports and give briefings.  Requires excellent analytical, 
communications and leadership skills.<P>

Send resume and letter to 
<A HREF="mailto:hrweb@tis.com">hrweb@tis.com</A>,
or FAX to 301-854-5363, ATTENTION: Human Resources.<P>

EEO/AA

