<HEAD><TITLE>TIS Rockville Jobs</TITLE></HEAD>
<!-- Copyright 1996 Trusted Information Systems -->
<!-- Design and programming: The James Gang (e-mail:jgang@jamesgang.com) --->

<body bgcolor="#FFFFFF" text="#000000" Link="#191970" VLink="#B22222" ALink="#B22222">

<center>
<a href="/docs/index.html">
<IMG width=378 height=27  SRC="/docs/images/tisbanner.gif" border=0 ALT="TIS"></A>
<HR  size=2 >
<a href="/docs/corporate/employ/index.html">
<IMG width=170 height=16 SRC="/docs/images/employ.gif" border=0 ALT="employment"></a>
</center>
<HR  size=2 >
<!-- Main Body -->
<P>
<Font Size=6>TIS Administrative Vacancies</FONT>
<BLOCKQUOTE>

<H3>Positions Open at TIS - Rockville, Maryland</H3>
<hr>
<A NAME="BUSOPS">
<H3>Commercial Consulting Business Operations Manager</A></H3><P>
Trusted Information Systems, Inc. has an immediate opening for a full time
Commercial Consulting Business Operations Manager in the Rockville, MD office.
<P>
Responsibilities include assisting in the development and implementation of
sales plans and supporting business plans necessary to establish and track
revenue and margin goal; managing preparation of budgets and forecasts for a
business operation; analyzing effects of budgets and forecasts and reports
to the manager; working with sales and senior management on a cross-
functional basis to achieve revenue and margin goals.
<P>
<b>Tasks Include:</b><p>
<UL>
Planning and implementing programs for the timely development and progress of
individuals of the  Commercial Consulting Group.  Assisting in the planning
and coordination of the compensation structures and changes as appropriate. 
<P>	
Supervising the development of the annual budget and monthly forecast for
the business operation, integrating product, marketing, and account strategies.
<P>
Presenting the budget and forecast to manager, identifying changes from
prior budgets and forecasts.
<P>	
Monitoring and reporting the performance of the budget, developing,
implementing and replicating  programs, and other activities that enhance
the achievement of the budget.
<P>	
Developing investment proposals for capital equipment and partnerships for
management review.
<P>	
Contributing to the process that establishes the pricing strategy for U.S.
Commercial Consulting operations.
<P>	
Developing one to two year revenue and margin operational plan.  Updating
the annual business model for the business operation.
<P>	
May be responsible for internal controls and reporting, and the
implementation of policies and procedures.
<P>	
Coordinating with the CFO and his designees in matters of financial planning
and analysis.
<P>	
Managing the consistent execution of Commercial Consulting Group business
policies and procedures, and recommending enhancements as appropriate.
<P>	
Managing and/or participating in task forces, special large projects,
committees, or team meetings.
<P>	
Establishing and/or participating in cross-functional relationships  to work
common goals.
<P>	
Performs other related duties as required.
</uL>	

<b>Management or Influence of People:</b><P>
Often expected to play a business partner role as a functional
representative within TIS.  Has influence across several organizations and
functions.  May  oversee multiple locations.  Contacts involve negotiating
and persuading, both inside and outside of TIS.
<P>
<b>Management</b><p>
Supports management of 25 to 50 employees or more. 
<P>	
<B>Role in Decision Making:</b><P>

Involved in operational and staff utilization planning.  Often provides
critical and prominent technical input to major decision-making  processes.  
<P>
<b>Scope of Problem Solving Complexity:</b><p>

Solving problems involving very complex technical issues across multiple
disciplines.  Problems, while unique,  are more tactical in nature, having
short-term implications of less than one year.  May work with technical
people outside of TIS in order to solve problems.
<P>
<B>Qualifications:</b><P> 

Needs to know TIS policies, markets, and processes.    May require
specialized functional knowledge.  Typically requires mastery to
state-of-the-art technical, functional, or business knowledge.  Emphasis of
the position is on depth of knowledge in a specialized area.
<P>
The successful candidate needs managerial and planning skills, as well as
skills in analysis, innovation, finance, communication, and negotiation.
<P>
For prompt consideration, please contact the Personnel Office. Send resume and letter to 
<A HREF="mailto:hrweb@tis.com">hrweb@tis.com</A>,
or FAX to 301-854-5363, ATTENTION: Human Resources.<P>

EEO/AA<hr> 
<A NAME="CONTADMIN">
<H3>Contract Administrator</A></H3><P>
Trusted Information Systems' Commercial Division, located in Rockville, MD,
has an immediate opening for a full-time Contract Administrator.  The
successful candidate must have 5+ years of related experience in contract
administration and must be familiar with commercial contract terms and
conditions in a high throughput, deadline-oriented sales organization.  
This person will support the Director of Contracts in the directorate's
contracting activities.  Export experience and paralegal training are a 
plus.<p>
For prompt consideration, please contact the Personnel Office. Send resume and letter to 
<A HREF="mailto:hrweb@tis.com">hrweb@tis.com</A>,
or FAX to 301-854-5363, ATTENTION: Human Resources.<P>

EEO/AA<hr> 

<A NAME="SYSADM">
<H3></A> System Administrator</H3><P>

Trusted Information Systems, Inc., a growing company specializing in computer and communications 
security, has an immediate opening in its Rockville, MD office for a Systems Administrator.  The successful 
candidate must have at least 4 years' experience as a professional systems administrator; strong interpersonal 
skills;  able to solve problems quickly and completely; and ability to work with minimal supervision within a 
team environment.  Must have solid understanding of UNIX, Windows 95 and NT operating systems; 
experience with, but not limited to, DNS, Sendmail, LAN, TCP/IP, Internet services, remote users and mobile users.<P>

Headquartered in MD, TIS has offices in VA, CA and London.  For interview consideration, send or fax 
resume with salary requirements to:<br>
<A HREF="mailto:hrweb@tis.com">hrweb@tis.com</A>,
or FAX to 301-854-5363, ATTENTION: Human Resources.<P>

EEO/AA
</BLOCKQUOTE>

