<P>
<Font Size=6>Gauntlet Internet Firewall Jobs</FONT>
<P>


<I>Trusted Information Systems, Inc.</I>
<BLOCKQUOTE>

<H3>Positions Open in the <A HREF="/docs/products/gauntlet/index.html">
Gauntlet Internet Firewall</A>
Group</H3>

<UL>
<LI><A HREF="#SoftDev">Software Developer</A>
<LI><A HREF="#Presales">Pre-sales Engineer</A> 
<LI><A HREF="#Support">Support Specialists</A> 
<LI><A HREF="#Shipping">Software Manufacturing and Shipping Specialist</A>
<LI><A HREF="#Release">Release Engineer</A>
<LI><A HREF="#Test">System Test/Quality Assurance Engineer</A>
<LI><A HREF="#NT">Windows NT Systems Programmer</A>
<LI><A HREF="#DOC">Documentation Specialist: Software Products</A>
<LI><A HREF="#SALES">Sales Coordinator</A>
<LI><A HREF="#ESALES">Entry Level Sales Assistant</A>
<LI><A HREF="#PSALES">Part-Time Entry Level Sales Assistant</A>
</UL>

<H3><A NAME="SoftDev"></A>Software Developer</H3>
Trusted Information Systems is seeking to hire experienced software 
developers to join the team implementing their Network Security Products,
including the Gauntlet (TM) Internet Firewall.  The work will involve
writing TCP/IP software, user interface software, or network applications
for releases on UNIX, NT, and Windows platforms. The position is located
in our Rockville, MD, facility.<P>

Candidates for this opening must have a Bachelor's Degree in a related
field and at least 2 years of applicable experience.  Knowledge of
the C language or TCP/IP or one or more of the following platforms: 
UNIX( BSD/os, SunOS, Solaris, HPUX),MS Windows(NT, '95, 3.1), development 
tools, and development methodology is required.  Other desirable skills or 
relevant experience include network software development, security, cryptography, or firewalls.  Experience in JAVA programming is also desired.
Candidates must possess good oral and written communication skills.<P>

Trusted Information Systems, Inc., (TIS), is a growing company specializing
in communications and computing security.  Headquartered in Glenwood, MD,
TIS has over 200 employees in offices in Glenwood, MD, Rockville, MD,
McLean, VA, Mountain View, CA, Los Angeles, CA, and London, England.  Staff
in all locations are involved in a variety of consulting research, and 
product development activities.  TIS offers excellent benefits and is an
Equal Opportunity Employer.<P>

For prompt consideration, please contact the Personnel Office or
send resume and letter to <A HREF="mailto:hrweb@tis.com">
hrweb@tis.com</A>,
or FAX to 301-854-5363, ATTENTION: Human Resources.<P>

EEO/AA<P>

<H3><A NAME="Presales"></A>Pre-sales Engineer</H3>

<P>
TIS has an exciting and challenging position available for a Pre-sales
Engineer based in the San Francisco Bay Area. This position involves
pre-sales support for TIS's Gauntlet Internet Firewall and other network
security products.<P>

The Pre-sales Engineer will work closely with the Sales Team to explain
TIS's security technology to prospective customers and will coordinate
product evaluations.<P>

The Western Region Team consists of senior-level players and offers an
exciting environment and a chance to deal with top tier customers.<P>

Technical requirements for the position are: firewall knowledge; Internet
experience; internetworking background; and a working knowledge of UNIX
administration.<P>

If interested, please contact Rick Maddox, Western Region Manager, (408)
395-3651 or <A HREF="mailto:maddox@tis.com">maddox@tis.com</A>.<P>

EEO/AA<P>

<H3><A NAME="Support"></A>Support Specialists</H3>

<P>
Trusted Information Systems has immediate openings in Rockville, Maryland
for full-time installation and telephone support persons working
in the Gauntlet Internet Firewall Group. These people are
responsible for installation, configuration, and customization
of Gauntlet Internet Firewall systems and for providing telephone
assistance to customers in answering questions about existing
installations. In-depth knowledge of UNIX&#174; system administration,
TCP/IP network configuration and management, Domain Name Service
configuration, and Sendmail configuration are required. Understanding
of standard network files and IP stack C code is a plus.
Telephone support experience is also a plus.<P>

Successful candidates must have good communication, analytical, and 
interpersonal skills and must be able work well independently with little 
supervision. Installations require some travel.<P>

For prompt consideration, please contact the Personnel Office or
send resume and letter to <A HREF="mailto:hrweb@tis.com">
hrweb@tis.com</A>,
or FAX to 301-854-5363, ATTENTION: Human Resources.<P>

EEO/AA<P>


<H3><A NAME="Shipping"></A>Software Manufacturing and Shipping Specialist</H3>
<P>
Trusted Information Systems/Rockville, MD facility, has an immediate opening
for  a software manufacturing and shipping specialist to join the team
producing Network Security Products, including the Gauntlet (TM) Internet
Firewall.  The work will involve all aspects of manufacturing and shipping
the software products and turnkey systems.  Specifically, the position
includes: <UL>
  <LI>  Shipping products (software, documentation, and other
                materials) to customers, prospective customers, and resellers.

  <LI>  Shipping beta products (software, documentation, and other
                materials) to customers, prospective customers, and resellers.

  <LI>  Coordinating the shipment of products via integrators.

  <LI>  Managing returns of products.

  <LI>  Maintaining inventories of documentation, software, hardware,
                and other materials.

  <LI>  Maintaining a database related to product shipping.

  <LI>  Coordinating media replication and documentation printing with
                outside vendors.

  <LI>  Working with leaders of development, documentation, marketing,
                product management, and sales administration to identify and
                implement alternative methods of product manufacturing and
                distribution.

  <LI>  Coordinating shipment and setup of equipment and systems for
                training courses<P></UL>

Candidates for this opening must have the following capabilities:<UL>

  <LI>  Ability to organize the shipping space and procedures.

  <LI>  Understanding of inventory control.

  <LI>  Experience with shipping and receiving hardware and software.

  <LI>  Understanding of basic computer hardware configuration.

  <LI>  Good English language communication skills, both verbal and
                written.

  <LI>  The ability to work well independently with little
                supervision.

</UL>

Knowledge of Microsoft software, specifically, Windows 3.1, Windows '95,
Windows NT, and Microsoft Office highly desirable.   Knowledge of PC hardware
and exposure to the UNIX operating system also desirable.<P>

If you are interested in applying your background to diverse projects
        in a small team environment, please send your resume including
        education history and relevant course work to: <A HREF="mailto:hrweb@tis.com">
        hrweb@tis.com</A> or by FAX to 301-854-5363, or by US Mail to: 
        Trusted Information Systems, Inc., 3060 Washington Road (Rt. 97), Glenwood,
        MD 21738<P>

EEO/AA<P>

