<H3><A NAME="TECH"></A>Technical Support Specialist</H3><P>

Trusted Information Systems, Inc. (NASDAQ:TISX), is a leading provider of 
comprehensive security solutions for protection of computer networks, 
including global Internet-based systems, internal networks and individual 
workstations and laptops.  The company develops, markets, licenses and 
supports the Gauntlet family of firewall products and other network 
security products, including cryptography and security consulting 
services for commercial and government customers.  The TIS home page 
on the World Wide Web is http://www.tis.com.<P>

The Los Angeles office of TIS has several openings for 
Internet Firewall Support Specialists who are responsible for:
<UL>
<LI> Providing email and telephone assistance to customers in answering
    questions regarding existing installations and configurations.

<LI> Potentially performing installation, configuration, and customization of 
    internet firewall systems.
</UL>
  Technical Requirements:
<UL>
<LI> In-depth knowledge of UNIX(R) system administration.
<LI> Solid understanding of TCP/IP network configuration and management.
<LI> Understanding of Domain Name Service (DNS) files and configuration.
<LI> Understanding of Sendmail files and configuration.
</UL>
  Greatly Desired:
<UL>
<LI> Previous technical support experience with complicated products.
<LI> Solid understanding of standard UNIX(R) network files.
<LI> Knowledge of IP stack C code.
<LI> Familiarity with routing protocols and techniques.
<LI> Familiarity with Windows '95 and NT software installation.
</UL>
  Non-technical Requirements:
<UL>
<LI> Customer-oriented attitude.
<LI> Excellent English language communication skills, both verbal and written.
<LI> Good analytical and interpersonal skills.
<LI> The ability to work well independently with little supervision.
</UL>
Nearterm plans may include after hours service through midnight and/or 
wearing a beeper for some portion of the week.<P>

TIS offers excellent benefits, educational reimbursement, and attractive
pay packages.  The Los Angeles Office is located in West LA near the
intersection of the 10 and 405 freeways.  <P>

Please provide your ASCII text (80 characters per line)
resume to:<a href="mailto:la-hro@tis.com"> la-hro@tis.com</a>.  Principals only, please.<P>
<HR>



<H3><A NAME="NETSECCON"></A>Network Security Consultant</H3><P>



The Commercial Consulting Group of Trusted Information Systems, Inc. is

seeking Security Analysts who can discuss network configuration and

hacker threats with system administrators, understand and formulate

network security policies and procedures, generate network topology

descriptions and illustrations, recognize security vulnerabilities,

recommend measures neces sary to counter the vulnerabilities, generate

clear and concise reports of their observations and recommendations,

and communicate with both technicians and managers.  Candidates must 

be familiar with Network Administration and Management

Tools, Hacker Activities and Techniques and Identification and

Authentication Mechanisms.  Other desirable experience includes Network

Protocols and Technology (e.g., Routers, Firewalls, Directory Services,

Network Security Mechanisms and Procedures).  Proof of US citizenship

required.<P>



If you are interested in applying your background to diverse projects

in a small team environment, please send your resume including

education history and relevant course work to: Trusted Information Systems, 11340 West Olympic Blvd., Suite 265,

Los Angeles, CA 90064, ATTN: HRO.  Fax: (310) 477-1998.

E-mail: <A HREF="mailto:la-hro@tis.com">la-hro@tis.com</A><P>



EEO/AA<P>



</BLOCKQUOTE>

