<HEAD><TITLE>Martha A. Branstad</TITLE></HEAD>
<!-- Copyright 1996 Trusted Information Systems -->
<!-- Design and programming: The James Gang (e-mail:jgang@jamesgang.com) -->

<body bgcolor="#FFFFFF" text="#000000" Link="#191970" VLink="#B22222" ALink="#B22222">

<center>
<a href="/docs/index.html">
<IMG width=378 height=27  SRC="/docs/images/tisbanner.gif" border=0 ALT="TIS"></A>
<HR  size=2 >
Executive Vice President, Director, Chief Operating Officer and President of the AR&E Division

</center>
<HR  size=2 >
<!-- Main Body -->
<BR>

<CENTER>
<IMG width=216 height=181 SRC="/docs/images/marty.gif" border=0 ALT="Martha A. Branstad">
</CENTER>

<Font Size=6>Martha A. Branstad</FONT>
<P>

<BLOCKQUOTE>

Martha A. Branstad has been Executive Vice President and a Director of the
Company since 1986, Chief Operating Officer of the Company since 1993, and
President of the AR&E Division since January 1996. Prior to joining TIS, she
served as the Program Director, Software Engineering, for the
National Science Foundation and was responsible for directing academic
research grants in software engineering and computational mathematics.
Earlier, Branstad held various management positions with the National Bureau of
Standards (now the National Institute of Standards and Technology),
including  Manager of Software for Parallel Processing and Manager of
Software Engineering. Prior to that, Branstad managed a software
research group for NSA. Branstad holds a B.S. in mathematics from
Iowa State University, an M.S. in mathematics from the University of
Wisconsin and a Ph.D. in computer science from Iowa State University.

<P>
E-mail: <a href="mailto:branstad@tis.com">branstad@tis.com</a>

<P>
