<HEAD><TITLE>Homayoon Tajalli</TITLE></HEAD>
<!-- Copyright 1996 Trusted Information Systems -->
<!-- Design and programming: The James Gang (e-mail:jgang@jamesgang.com) -->

<body bgcolor="#FFFFFF" text="#000000" Link="#191970" VLink="#B22222" ALink="#B22222">

<center>
<a href="/docs/index.html">
<IMG width=378 height=27  SRC="/docs/images/tisbanner.gif" border=0 ALT="TIS"></A>
<HR  size=2 >
 Executive Vice President; General Manager, Cryptographic Products
</center>
<HR  size=2 >
<!-- Main Body -->
<BR>

<CENTER>
<IMG width=216 height=181 SRC="/docs/images/tj.gif" border=0 ALT="Homayoon Tajalli">
</CENTER>

<Font Size=6>Homayoon Tajalli</FONT>
<P>

<BLOCKQUOTE>
With 17 years of senior technical and management experience in the computer field, Homayoon Tajalli is an Executive Vice President and has been with the Company since 1987.  Mr. Tajalli was the Project Manager and Chief Architect of the Trusted Mach (TMach) Operating System project from its inception until December 1995.  Since January 1996, he has served as the General Manager of the Cryptographic Products Line, with responsibility for the Company's Key Recovery Technology (KRT). His other accomplishments at TIS include managing all aspects of the Trusted XENIX B2 OS and TMEG line of high-assurance Mail Guard products.  Prior to joining TIS, Mr. Tajalli held various senior management positions with Digital Equipment Corporation, including Senior Software Manager responsible for the MCI Mail project, the "grandfather" of many of today's on-line electronic services. Mr. Tajalli holds B.S. and M.S. degrees in electrical engineering from the University of Maryland and is a graduate of General Electric's Advance Edison Engineering program.
