<HTML>
<HEAD><TITLE>Frederick M. Avolio</TITLE></HEAD>
<!-- Copyright 1996 Trusted Information Systems -->
<!-- Design and programming: The James Gang (e-mail:jgang@jamesgang.com) -->

<body bgcolor="#FFFFFF" text="#000000" Link="#191970" VLink="#B22222" ALink="#B22222">

<center>
<a href="/docs/index.html">
<IMG width=378 height=27  SRC="/docs/images/tisbanner.gif" border=0 ALT="TIS"></A>
<HR  size=2 >
Vice President of Technology Marketing
</center>
<HR  size=2 >
<!-- Main Body -->
<BR>

<CENTER>
<IMG width=216 height=181 SRC="/docs/images/avolio.gif" border=0 ALT="Frederick M. Avolio">
</CENTER>

<Font Size=6>Frederick M. Avolio</FONT>
<P>

<BLOCKQUOTE>

Frederick M. Avolio is TIS Vice President of Technology Marketing. He has been 
active in TIS' network security consulting and was product manager for TIS' 
Gauntlet Internet Firewall. He has lectured and consulted on Internet gateways
 and firewalls, Internet security, and electronic mail configuration for both 
government and industry organizations.  He has worked in the UNIX and TCP/IP 
communities since 1979 and is a well-known speaker and contributor to DECUS, 
USENIX, and other security-related forums. Prior to joining TIS, Avolio was a 
senior consultant and senior manager with Digital Equipment Corporation. Among
 other duties there, he managed and maintained one of DEC's Internet gateways 
and was instrumental in productizing Digital's Internet firewall product. 
Earlier, he worked at NSA, supporting UNIX systems, specializing in electronic 
mail. Avolio is the co-author, with Paul Vixie, of SENDMAIL: THEORY AND 
PRACTICE published by Digital Press. He has an undergraduate degree in 
Computer Science from the University of Dayton and a Master of Science from 
Indiana University.
<P>
E-mail: <a href="mailto:avolio@tis.com">avolio@tis.com</a>

