<Font Size=6>William C. Barker</FONT>
<P>

<BLOCKQUOTE>

William C. Barker is Vice President for the Commercial Consulting Practice at TIS, where he manages network security analyses and policy consulting, research advisory and technology delivery, and training groups. Mr. Barker formerly coordinated the corporation's government multilevel systems security consulting and government certification and accreditation activities and also directed the company's Independent Research and Development (IR&D) program; managed system accreditation contract activities; oversaw the design of trusted operating system interfaces to commercial and government cryptographic devices; and conducted integrity policy definition and modeling activities. Mr. Barker has been a computer security professional since 1966, when he began his career at NSA, and is a member of AFCEA and IEEE.
