<HEAD><TITLE>R. William Thompson</TITLE></HEAD>
<!-- Copyright 1996 Trusted Information Systems -->
<!-- Design and programming: The James Gang (e-mail:jgang@jamesgang.com) -->

<body bgcolor="#FFFFFF" text="#000000" Link="#191970" VLink="#B22222" ALink="#B22222">

<center>
<a href="/docs/index.html">
<IMG width=378 height=27  SRC="/docs/images/tisbanner.gif" border=0 ALT="TIS"></A>
<HR  size=2 >
Vice President of Business Development for the Commercial Division
</center>
<HR  size=2 >
<!-- Main Body -->
<BR>

<CENTER>
<IMG width=216 height=182 SRC="/docs/images/thompson.gif" border=0 ALT="R. William Thompson">
</CENTER>

<Font Size=6>R. William Thompson</FONT>
<P>

<BLOCKQUOTE>

R. William Thompson is TIS Vice President of Business Development for the Commercial Division (CKE) and has worked in high-technology management, sales, and marketing since 1969.  Mr. Thompson has a history of successes in start-up companies as well as established small and large corporations. Previously, he worked for Microelectronics and Computer Technology Corporation (MCC) as Director of Commercial Business Development and was the CEO of an MCC spin-off company that developed middleware to unify incompatible database environments. His experience spans general management, strategic product planning/management, domestic and international marketing, direct and indirect sales channels, business development, and customer service for companies such as RCA Computer Systems, Perkin Elmer Data Systems, and Apollo Computer. He holds a BS in Electrical Engineering and an MS in Industrial Engineering/Computer Science, both from the University of South Florida.
<P>
E-mail: <a href="mailto:thompson@tis.com">thompson@tis.com</a>

