<HEAD><TITLE>
Gauntlet&#174 Now Runs On HP MC/ ServiceGuard 
</TITLE>

<!-- Copyright 1996 Trusted Information Systems -->
<!-- Design and programming: The James Gang (jgang@jamesgang.com) -->
</HEAD>

<BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF" text="#000000" Link="#191970" VLink="#B22222" 
ALink="#B22222">

<center>
<a href="/docs/index.html">
<IMG width=378 height=27
SRC="/docs/images/tisbanner.gif" border=0
ALT="TIS"></A>
<HR  size=2 >
<a href="/docs/corporate/press/index.html">
<IMG width=95 height=16
SRC="/docs/images/pr.gif" border=0
ALT="press"></a>
</center>
<HR  size=2 >

<!-- Main Body -->


<Font size= 5>
Gauntlet&#174 Internet Firewall Now Runs On HP MC/ ServiceGuard 

</Font>
<P>

<Blockquote>

<i>Firewall Is the First to Enable High-Availability Security With HP MC/ServiceGuard</i>
<p>
Glenwood, MD January 14, 1997 -- 
Trusted Information Systems (NASDAQ:TISX) today announced
that its Gauntlet&#174; Internet Firewall supports the HP MC/ServiceGuard, HP's
high-availability platform.  This provides an "always-available" Gauntlet
firewall gateway by linking together two computers which have redundant
hardware.
<P>

The MC/ServiceGuard software instantly shifts operations to a backup system,

in the event one hardware component fails, allowing for little-to-no

interruption in service.  TIS now allows the same peace of mind for a

network security system running on HP-UX: if operations are forced to shift

to another piece of hardware, the firewall will as well.<P>


According to Harvey Weiss, President of the TIS Commercial Division, "This

new capability ensures that security is maintained even in situations of

extraordinary stress.  We're delighted to be able to make high-availability

security possible."<P>


Joaquin Ruiz, HP product manager for MC/ServiceGuard commented, "Gauntlet is

the first firewall to be tested on our high-availability platform, and we

think that it provides an exciting security solution in combination with our

platform."<P>

The new enhancement comes on the heels of several TIS announcements at the

end of 1996, including the availability of Authenticode&#153;

verification and the introduction of the world's first full-service web

server security product, ForceField&#153;.
<P>
<B>About Trusted Information Systems, Inc.</B><P>
Trusted Information Systems, Inc., is a leading provider of comprehensive security solutions for protection of computer networks, including global Internet-based systems, internal networks and individual workstations and laptops. The company develops, markets, licenses and supports the Gauntlet family of firewall products and other network security products, and provides cryptography and security consulting training, advanced research and engineering, and services for commercial and government customers. For more information, contact TIS at (301) 527-9500.
The TIS home page on the World Wide Web is http://www.tis.com
<HR>


<I>For more information, please contact:<P></I>
