<!-- Main Body -->


<Font size= 5>
Trusted Information Systems Offers New Security Consulting 
Services

</Font>
<P>

<Blockquote>

		
<b>TIS Expertise in Vulnerability Assessment, Policy Development, System Installation and 
Training Now Gives Customers Added Flexibility</b><p>
 
Glenwood, MD  January 14, 1997 -- Trusted Information Systems 
(NASDAQ:TISX) today announced the expansion of the consulting services 
offered by its Commercial Consulting Group.  TIS now offers a wider 
array of standardized services that customers can purchase through 
multiple distribution channels enabling one-stop shopping for both 
security products and services.<p>

"Given the rapid evolution of client/server and Internet, intranet and

extranet business applications, even many large organizations now lack the

expertise required to implement secure networks," remarked Harvey Weiss,

President of the TIS Commercial Division.  "By increasing our consulting

service offerings, we can now provide our customers with more choices for

protecting valuable information system resources."<p>

The Gauntlet Firewall Remote Audit and Verification is just one of the many

new services offered by TIS.  Subscribing to this service entitles consumers

to periodic verification by TIS and added assurance that they can maintain

the best possible configuration for their firewall at all times, not just on

the day it was purchased and installed.<p>

TIS provides over 20 different services, including custom consulting,

network vulnerability scans, firewall installation, and security policy

development.  Training services are offered in TIS classroom facilities as

well as on site at customer locations throughout North America.<p>

<b>About Trusted Information Systems, Inc.</b><p>
Trusted Information Systems, Inc., is a leading provider of 
comprehensive security solutions for protection of computer 
networks, including global Internet-based systems, internal 
networks and individual workstations and laptops. The company 
develops, markets, licenses and supports the Gauntlet family 
of firewall products and other network security products, 
and provides cryptography and security consulting training, 
advanced research and engineering, and services for commercial 
and government customers. For more information, contact TIS at 
(301) 527-9500. The TIS home page on the World Wide Web is 
http://www.tis.com

