<HEAD>
<TITLE>Gauntlet&#174; Firewall Now Available For Windows NT&#174;</TITLE>
<!-- Copyright 1996 Trusted Information Systems -->
<!-- Design and programming: The James Gang (jgang@jamesgang.com) -->
</HEAD>

<BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF" text="#000000" Link="#191970" VLink="#B22222" 
ALink="#B22222">

<center>
<a href="http://www.tis.com/docs/index.html">
<IMG SRC="http://www.tis.com/docs/images/gtop.gif" border=0>
<HR  size=2 >
<a href="/docs/corporate/press/index.html">
<IMG width=95 height=16
SRC="http://www.tis.com/docs/images/pr.gif" border=0
ALT="press"></a>
</center>
<HR  size=2 >

<!-- Main Body -->
<H2>Gauntlet&#174; Firewall Now Available For Windows NT&#174;</H2><br>
<i>TIS Now Bringing Comprehensive Security Solutions to NT Environments</i>
<P>
Glenwood, MD,  December 9, 1996 -- Trusted Information Systems, Inc. (Nasdaq:  TISX) 
     today announced the availability of its Gauntlet&#174; Internet Firewall 
     for the Windows NT&#174; environment.  The new addition to the Gauntlet 
     firewall family combines the security and quality that the market has 
     come to expect from the Gauntlet product line with the ease of use of 
     the NT platform.  The first shipment of Gauntlet NT-based firewalls is 
     scheduled for December 1996.
<P>
The Windows NT version of the Gauntlet firewall takes full advantage 
     of the NT environment, including use of threads.  As a result, 
     firewall performance is enhanced and the Gauntlet NT firewall will 
     scale readily to multiprocessor platforms.  The new firewall also 
     offers a superior NT Graphic User Interface.  It supports version 4.0 
     of NT Advanced Server and will support all future versions.
<P>
"TIS is strongly committed to supporting customers who work in the 
     rapidly growing NT environment," remarked Harvey Weiss, President of 
     TIS's Commercial Division. "We are working closely with Microsoft on a 
     comprehensive set of security solutions in addition to the firewall, 
     such as Authenticode(tm) signature verification.The result is, and will 
     be, unprecedented security capabilities for our customers who operate 
     on NT."
<P>     
     In a related announcement, TIS has announced availability of ActiveX 
     and Java signature verification for the entire Gauntlet firewall 
     family, including Unix and Windows NT&#174; versions. ActiveX and Java 
     signature verification will protect against viruses in ActiveX 
     executables and Java applets using Microsoft's Authenticode 
     technology.  Authenticode is available on all Gauntlet Internet 
     Firewall operating systems.
<P>
