<HTML>
<HEAD><TITLE>Network Security Survey</TITLE>
<!-- Copyright 1996 Trusted Information Systems -->
<!-- Design and programming: The James Gang (jgang@jamesgang.com) --->
</HEAD>

<body bgcolor="#FFFFFF" text="#000000" Link="#191970" VLink="#B22222" ALink="#B22222">

<center>
<a href="/docs/products/consulting/index.html">
<IMG width=230 height=33  SRC="/docs/images/tisc.gif" border=0 ALT="tis consulting"></A>
<HR  size=2 >
<IMG width=112 height=15  SRC="/docs/images/nsecurity.gif" border=0 ALT="consulting">
</center>

<HR  size=2 >

<!-- Main Body -->

<Font size= 6>Network Security Survey</FONT>

<BLOCKQUOTE>

<H3>Network Security Survey Service Description</H3>

Trusted Information Systems will conduct an analysis of your networking environment and current security posture. Depending on your requirements, you can chose to have us focus on:

<TABLE>
	<TR> 
	<TD> 
<IMG width=155 height=136 SRC="/docs/images/barker3.gif" border=0 ALT="TIS staff">	

	</TD> 
	<TD>
	<UL>
	<LI>	Perimeter Network and External Connections
	<LI>	Corporate Data Center
	<LI>	Host-based Security
	<LI>	Internal LAN-WAN Connectivity
	<LI>	Overall Corporate Security Architecture
	<LI>	Entire Computing Installation 
</UL>

	</TD> 
	</TR>
</TABLE>


<P>
<B>Survey Process</B><BR>
		We conduct a site inspection, interview your staff, review architecture and configuration documentation, analyze connectivity and access controls, and study security policies, choices and goals in the context of your business needs. The consultants will identify vulnerabilities, and recommend corrections, solutions, and implementation priorities in both documentary and briefing formats.	
<P>
<B>Pre-Inspection</B><BR>
	In advance of the site visit, we usually ask our contact in your organization to distribute a questionnaire to individuals in the following functional roles: network security management and administration; technical support and Help Desk; data center managers and large server/database administrators; communications and telecommunications engineers; auditors; and management. The intent of the questionnaire is to elicit basic configuration information, as well as to stimulate thinking on network security issues (connectivity, access control, vulnerabilities) in advance of the on-site interviews. 
<P>


<B>The Site Visit</B><BR>
	The site visit by two TIS analysts usually lasts two to five days. We will work with you prior to the visit to establish an agenda for on-site interviews and tours of operational areas. In the interviews, company representatives should be prepared to discuss hardware and software configurations, technology trends, business goals, data sensitivity, security measures and goals, current security policies, disaster recovery and intrusion detection and response planning, and access control. The site visit will not involve any type of penetration testing or automated network auditing activity (although TIS offers these as separate services). Large, complex installations may require multiple visits, or visits to multiple sites.

<P>
<B>Follow-up</B><BR>
	Following the on-site visit, TIS will prepare a draft report of the survey findings, analysis and recommendations. Follow-up questions are usually handled by telephone or electronic mail (where appropriate). The report will provide a general overview of  your computing and network environment, and your current information security posture. It will discuss threats to your security, and the risks which these threats may pose, as well as detailed observations regarding specific security issues brought to light during the survey. We will point out vulnerabilities, discuss the tradeoffs among cost, ease of use, business requirements and acceptable levels of risk, and make recommendations for improvements. Whenever possible, we will also include relevant white papers and information on useful tools and techniques.
<P>
	You will have thirty days to review the draft document, and recommend changes where necessary.  If requested, TIS will provide an Executive Briefing on the survey methodology and results.
<P>
<HR>

