<HTML>
<HEAD><TITLE>Research Advisory Service</TITLE>
<!-- Copyright 1996 Trusted Information Systems -->
<!-- Design and programming: The James Gang (jgang@jamesgang.com) --->
</HEAD>

<body bgcolor="#FFFFFF" text="#000000" Link="#191970" VLink="#B22222" ALink="#B22222">

<center>
<a href="/docs/products/consulting/index.html">
<IMG width=230 height=33  SRC="/docs/images/tisc.gif" border=0 ALT="tis consulting"></A>
<HR  size=2 >
<IMG width=126 height=16  SRC="/docs/images/ras.gif" border=0 ALT="Research Advisory Service">
</center>

<HR  size=2 >

<!-- Main Body -->

<Font size= 6>Information Security Research Advisory Service</FONT>

<BLOCKQUOTE>

<H3>Overview</H3>
Successful businesses today are those that can take advantage of technological advances and rapidly respond to customer needs. More and more companies are entering into electronic business relationships with customers, suppliers, and partners. Seamless connectivity can reduce time to market, cost of goods sold, and open new revenue streams. However, the down side of this rapid integration of, and dependency on, communications technology is greatly increased vulnerability to electronic intrusion, theft, and vandalism.
<P>
As a world leader in the Information Security field, Trusted Information Systems has been helping businesses and government agencies assure the integrity of their information systems since 1983. Drawing on the work of more than 100 information security experts at TIS, the Research Advisory Service provides organizations with near real-time analysis of the security impact of emerging technologies, threats, products, and standards. RAS customers receive electronic (or hard copy) bulletins and tailored InfoFlashes, as well as custom consulting support. The TIS RAS provides businesses with the timely information and guidance required to take advantage of technology without putting critical information systems at risk.
<P>
<HR>
<H3>Trusted Information Systems</H3>
With 250 employees dedicated to advancing the state of the practice of information security, Trusted Information Systems is a world leader in computer and communications security. TIS customers include Fortune 100 companies across a wide spectrum of industry segments, as well as all major government agencies. Headquartered in Glenwood MD, TIS also has offices in Virginia, California, and the UK.
<P>
TIS has been developing firewalls, secure operating systems, electronic mail software, and encryption systems since 1983. Along with security research and products, TIS offers custom consulting support for vulnerability analysis, policy development, incident response, and software development. The TIS Research Advisory Service draws upon this pool of expertise and information sources to provide timely, targeted guidance on both tactical and strategic security issues.
<P>
<HR>
<H3>Research Advisory Service</H3>
Every business decision flows through three major cycles: strategize, implement, and measure/audit. TIS' Research Advisory Service provides support to all phases:

<OL>
<LI><B>Strategic Analysis</B>
<UL><LI>Technology Trends <LI>Emerging Standards <LI>Threat Analyses <LI>Decision Support Models </UL>
<P>
<LI><B>Implementation Issues</B>
<UL><LI>Case Studies <LI>Vendor Mapping <LI>Cost of Use Analyses</UL>
<P>
<LI><B>Performance Measurement</B>
<UL><LI>Comparison of Intrusion Detection Tools <LI>Return on Investment Models <LI>Policy Completeness <LI>Analysis Templates</UL>
</OL>

<BR>
The TIS RAS delivers this support through a variety of services tailored to the unique needs of each organization.
<P>
<HR>

<H3>RAS Deliverables</H3>
The TIS RAS provides a mixture of near real-time information services, in depth analysis of strategic issues, and on-call consulting for advice and recommendations across the spectrum of information security issues. RAS deliverables provide advice and recommendations tailored to the needs of your organization:

<BLOCKQUOTE>

<B>Trusted Updates</B> - Monthly bulletins, delivered via email or postal mail, on topics such as electronic commerce, Internet/WWW security, secure remote access, encryption use, integration of digital signatures, etc. Trusted Updates provide decision support models, technology evaluations, standards analysis, and case studies of business use of information security technologies.
<P>
<B>Trusted Flashes</B> - Delivered via electronic mail (fax at extra cost), Trusted Flashes provide customers with TIS analysis of breaking events. Flashes are produced as events warrant, generally averaging once per week. Topics include vulnerability and threat alerts, vendor announcement analysis, and evaluations of standards developments or other industry events.
<P>
<B>TeleConferences</B> - Audio teleconferences are scheduled quarterly, to allow TIS customers to interact with each other and with experts in security topics. TIS publishes the schedule of topics each quarter; custom teleconferences are available as part of the Advisory services
<P>
<B>Advisory Services</B> - Each RAS client has a Research Director assigned to their service, with a retainer account established for on-call consultation. TIS Research Directors are available via email, telephone, or fax, and will call upon TIS' InfoSec resources and their own background to provide high impact recommendations to your organization.
<P>
<B>Knowledge Base Access</B> - World Wide Web access is available to all TIS research deliverables, white papers, models, templates, and other information. TIS uses the Excite search engine to provide concept and keyword based searching of the InfoSec knowledge base.

</BLOCKQUOTE>
<HR>
 <P>
<H3>Pricing Structure</H3>

The TIS Research Advisory Service is available through yearly subscription, in four standard packages. The Research Delivery service provides research reports and Trusted flashes only, and is priced for academic/non-profit organizations. The Research Advisory Service adds WWW access, teleconferences, and on-call consulting support at three different levels:
<P>

<TABLE BORDER=1 CELLPADDING=4>
<TR><TD><B>Feature</B> </TD> <TD><B>Research Reports</B></TD> <TD><B>Trusted Flashes</B> </TD> <TD><B>WWW Access</B></TD> <TD><B>Teleconferences</B></TD><TD><B>Consulting</B></TD></TR>

<TR><TD>Level 1 </TD> <TD>Monthly</TD> <TD>All</TD> <TD>Limited </TD> <TD>None</TD><TD>35 hours</TD></TR>

<TR><TD>Level 2 </TD> <TD>Monthly</TD> <TD>All</TD> <TD>Full </TD> <TD>2 per year</TD><TD>60 hours</TD></TR>

<TR><TD>Level 3 </TD> <TD>Monthly</TD> <TD>All</TD> <TD>Full </TD> <TD>4 per year</TD><TD>150 hours</TD></TR>
</TABLE>
<P>
Other service levels are available on a custom basis. A discount structure is available for organizations purchasing other TIS products and services.
<P>
<HR>

