<HTML>
<HEAD><TITLE>Firewall Monitoring and Verification Services</TITLE>
<!-- Copyright 1996 Trusted Information Systems -->
<!-- Design and programming: The James Gang (jgang@jamesgang.com) --->
</HEAD>

<body bgcolor="#FFFFFF" text="#000000" Link="#191970" VLink="#B22222" ALink="#B22222">

<center>
<a href="/docs/products/consulting/index.html">
<IMG width=230 height=33  SRC="/docs/images/tisc.gif" border=0 ALT="tis consulting"></A>
<HR  size=2 >
<IMG width=184 height=16  SRC="/docs/images/monitor.gif" border=0 ALT="Monitoring and Verification">
</center>

<HR  size=2 >

<!-- Main Body -->

<Font size= 6>Firewall Monitoring and Verification Services</FONT>
<BLOCKQUOTE>
<B>Overview</B><BR>

For Gauntlet firewall users, Trusted Information System's Commercial Consulting Group provides several standard service offerings to assure the integrity of Gauntlet installation and configuration. Contact your TIS sales representative or send electronic mail to survey@tis.com for more information.
<P>
<B>Remote Gauntlet Post-Installation Review (SFPR)</B><BR>
The Gauntlet Post-Installation Review is designed for clients who have installed and configured a Gauntlet firewall themselves.  TIS will perform a post-installation review to verify proper firewall configuration.  The review will encompass a brief analysis of  the physical connectivity as well as ensure consistency with a client's corporate security policy.  This service is available for Gauntlet V3.1 and later.  It is recommended that Gauntlet Audit and Verification Services (SFAV) be considered as an adjunct to this service.
<P>

<B>Gauntlet Audit and Verification Service (SFAV)</B><BR>

TIS will provide a Gauntlet Firewall site with regular verification of the firewall configuration to provide assurance against security policy inconsistencies and inadvertent configuration errors. This review includes a brief survey of the physical network and its impact on the firewall.  Monthly, quarterly and annual service options are available.  TIS Audit and Verification Service is available for Gauntlet V3.1 and later.  For maximum benefit, we recommend combining this service with an Internet Connectivity Vulnerability Analysis (SCVA) and/or a Network Vulnerability Scan (SNVS).

<P>
<HR>

