<HTML>
<HEAD><TITLE>Trust Engineering</title>
<!-- Copyright 1996 Trusted Information Systems -->
<!-- Design and programming: The James Gang (jgang@jamesgang.com) -->
</HEAD>

<body bgcolor="#FFFFFF" text="#000000" Link="#191970" VLink="#B22222" ALink="#B22222">

<center>
<a href="/docs/products/consulting/index.html">
<IMG width=230 height=33  SRC="/docs/images/tisc.gif" border=0 ALT="TIS Consulting"></A>
<HR  size=2 >
<IMG width=120 height=16 SRC="/docs/images/engineer.gif" border=0 ALT="Trust Engineering">
</center>

<HR  size=2 >

<!-- Main Body -->

<Font size= 6>Trust Engineering</font>
<Blockquote>
TIS staff has over 13 years of experience in developing and
evaluating systmes based on national and international security criteria. Having participated in both the
development and evaluation sides of the National Computer Security Center's (NCSC's) Trusted Product Evaluation Program
(TPEP) and supported the development of multilevel secure (MLS) systems, TIS can provide the unique ability to create solutions that meet all
the necessary technical requirements while remaining sensitive to vendor
constraints, i.e., cost, scheduling, manpower, etc.

<P>
<CENTER>
<IMG width=338 height=48 SRC="/docs/images/bawotanim2.gif" border=0 ALT="Building a World of Trust">
</CENTER>
<P>
TIS has successfully participated in the evaluation process involving many
unique and previously unexplored efforts.  TIS is supporting the design and development MLS avionics system for the Advanced Tactical Fighter (F-22).  TIS was the first operating system
(O/S) vendor to create a process that facilitated the B2 evaluation of
multiple clone hardware platforms.  This effort was instrumental in
demonstrating that NCSC's
 Rating Maintenance (RAMP) can work for higher-level
systems.  The clone effort was followed by two RAMP activities resulting in
the first evaluated INFOSEC solution, integrating two COMSEC and COMPUSEC
products.

<HR>
<H3>A unique, proactive approach</H3>
Our unique, proactive approach has proven very successful for handling the
evaluation of new and innovative technologies for current state-of-the-art
concerns and the resolution of tough technical issues.  The following
summarizes some of the ways in which we can apply our knowledge base and
approach to your evaluation effort.  TIS can:

<UL>
	<LI>Provide expert guidance on issues related to satisfying the TCSEC
	System Architecture for any class (C2-A1) of system.  We have proven
	experience in areas of modularity, layering, data hiding, least
	privilege, and TCB minimization.
<p>
	<LI>Provide assistance with the TCSEC Design Specification and
	Verification (DS&V) requirements and latest related interpretations
	for all types and classes of systems.
<p>
	<li>Produce and/or review informal
	and formal models, subject/object studies,  DTLSs, formal
	specifications, and mappings among elements of DS&V evidence.
<p>
	<LI>Provide assistance with the TCSEC Test Requirements.  This can
	include creating test scripts and producing test documentation such
	as Test Plans, Test Descriptions, and Test Procedures.  Assist in
	test coverage analysis.  We have experience with Penetration Testing
	and can provide penetration test as well as functional test
	solutions.
<p>
	<LI>Perform Covert Channel Analysis for B2+ systems.  
<p>
	<LI>Develop and present classes on trust and evaluation issues (e.g.,
	design documentation, covert channel analysis, configuration
	management, etc.) at the customer's site.
<p>
	<LI>Assist in the preparation for a Preliminary Technical Review
	(PTR), including completion of the PTR Questionnaire.
<p>
	<LI>Generate RAMP Maintenance Plan and support RAMP efforts.  Assist
	with the generation and presentation of RAMP evidence.
<p>
	<LI>Provide assistance with the resolution of issues raised by the
	evaluation team.
<p>
	<LI>Ascertain the impact of C2-A1 requirements on new and existing
	systems.
<p>
	<LI>Provide strategies for evolution from C2 to B1+ classes of the
	TCSEC.
</UL>

<HR>
