<HTML>
<HEAD><TITLE>GAUNTLET® FIREWALL FAMILY INSTALLATION, CONFIGURATION AND MANAGEMENT </TITLE></HEAD>
<!-- Copyright 1996 Trusted Information Systems -->
<!-- Design and programming: The James Gang (e-mail:jgang@jamesgang.com) --->

<body bgcolor="#FFFFFF" text="#000000" Link="#191970" VLink="#B22222" ALink="#B22222">

<center>
<a href="/docs/products/consulting/index.html">
<IMG width=230 height=33  SRC="/docs/images/tisc.gif" border=0 ALT="tis consulting"></A>
<HR  size=2 >
<IMG width=123 height=16  SRC="/docs/images/training.gif" border=0 ALT="Training Services">
</center>

<HR  size=2 >

<!-- Main Body -->

<Font size= 6>Gauntlet&#174; Firewall Family<br>
Installation, Configuration, and Management </font><br>
(Two Day Course)
<P>
<BLOCKQUOTE>


<b>Focus</b><br>

This fast-paced, two-day class focuses specifically on the installation, configuration, and management 
of the Gauntlet&#174; Internet Firewall. It offers an overview of basic firewall design concepts, network configurations, 
and Gauntlet Internet Firewall features and characteristics. There is hands-on training in installation and configuration, 
as well as management of the Gauntlet Internet Firewall.
<P>

<b>Who Should Attend</b><br>

This class is targeted at those individuals whose companies have purchased the Gauntlet Internet Firewall 
and who will be doing the installation, configuration and/or management of the firewall. Basic knowledge of 
TCP/IP networking concepts is assumed.<P>

<HR>
<p>
<b>Day One Overview</b><br> 
(Basic Installation and Configuration)<br>
The first day of training is focused on those individuals who plan to install the Gauntlet Internet Firewall themselves. Basic 
knowledge of TCP/IP networking concepts is assumed. The hands-on portion of the class is held in a LAN environment.
<P>
<B>Opening</B><P> 					
		
<b>I.	Information Security Review</b>
<UL>
<LI>Vulnerability points 
<LI>Threats
<LI>Countermeasures
</UL>

<b>II.	Firewall Architectures</b>
<UL>
<LI>Packet Filters
<LI>Application Gateways
</UL>

<b>III.	The Gauntlet Internet Firewall </b>
<UL>
<LI>Preinstall Questionnaire
<LI>Assuring Connectivity (ef0, ef1, etc.)
<LI>Establishing User Authentication
<LI>Services/Proxies
<LI>Reports
<LI>Day-to-Day operations
</uL>

<b>IV.	Network Designs</b>

<b>V.	Routing, DNS and Mail</b>
<UL>
<LI>IP Addressing
<LI>Transparency
<LI>Static vs. Dynamic Routing
</UL>

<b>VI.	Basic Installation and Configuration</b>
<UL>
<LI>Loading Gauntlet s/w on standard O/S
<LI>Application notes, permission problems, partitioning
<LI>Booting
<LI>The GUI
<LI>Using the Menu
<LI>Basic Configuration
</UL>

<HR>	
<P>
<b>Day Two Overview</b><br> 
(Customizing Proxies and Management)<br>Day Two builds on Day One and is
 based on an installed Gauntlet Internet Firewall. The focus is on non-standard 
proxy settings and on the proper daily network security administration and 
maintenance functions of the firewall.
<P>
<b>VII.	Configuring Proxies using the netperm-table</b>
<UL>
<LI>Examples:<BR>
					SMTP<BR>
					Telnet<BR>
					FTP<BR>
					HTTP/SHTTP<BR>
					Plug-gw, incl. newsfeeds<BR>
					LP<BR>
</UL>

<b>VIII.	User Authentication</b>
<UL>
<LI>SecurID, S/Key, SNK, CryptoCard, etc.
</UL>

<b>IX.	Reports</b>	
<UL>
<LI>Logs
<LI>Audits
<LI>Alerts
</UL>

<b>X.	Remote Management</b>
<UL>
<LI>Gauntlet Intranet Firewall
<LI>Net Extender
<LI>PC Extender
</UL>

<b>XI.	Day-to-Day System Management</b>
<UL>
<LI>Backups
<LI>Upgrades
<LI>Integrity Checks
<LI>Troubleshooting
</UL>
	
<b>XII.	Open Lab</b>

<p>
</blockquote>
<hr>
<b>Course Information</b>

<blockquote>
<a href="gicm.html">Installation, Configuration and Management 
Course Description</a><br>
<a href="mns.html">Managing Network Security Course Description</a><br>
</blockquote>
