<B>Issue 64/October 95</B>
<P>

This issue features articles on selected sessions of the 1995 National
Information Systems Security Conference (NISSC) held in Baltimore, MD,
October 10 - 13, 1995.
	<UL>
<BR>

		<LI>1995 National Computer Security Award Winner: Dr. Dennis K. Branstad

		<LI>Keynote Address for NISSC '95: Information Infrastructure: Evolution and Expectations

		<LI>Perspectives on Internet Security Evaluation and Assurance

		<LI>Key Escrow Panel

		<LI>Crime I: Legal Hacking: What Is Computer Crime?

		<LI>Internet Security: Current Threats and Practical Solutions

		<LI>Cryptographic Application Program Interfaces Session

		<LI>Session on Encipherment

	</UL>
<P>
<BR>

<B>Issue 65/November 95</B>


This issue features a review of the ICE workshop and 
3 articles continuing our coverage of the 1995 NISS Conference

	<UL>

		<LI>Summary of Second International Cryptographic Experiment (ICE) Workshop

		<LI>NISSC Panel Session: Security on the I-WAY (High Speed ATM Networks)

		<LI>NISSC Session: Case Studies I: Solutions

		<LI>System Security Engineering Capability Maturity Model (SSE-CMM)

	</UL>
<P>
<BR>

<B>Issue 66/December 95</B>

	<UL>


		<LI>Global Cryptography Policy: Special coverage of a recent landmark meeting in Paris

		<LI>Interview with Steve Cobb

		<LI>Book Review: Building Internet Firewalls
		
		<LI>Internet Security Resources Reference List

		<LI>Security Policy: What to Say and How to Say It

	</UL>

