<HTML>
<HEAD>
<TITLE>TIS/DMS Firewall Plus</TITLE>

<head>
<!-- Copyright 1996 Trusted Information Systems -->
<!-- Design and programming: The James Gang (jgang@jamesgang.com) -->
</HEAD>

<body bgcolor="#FFFFFF" text="#000000" 
Link="#191970" VLink="#B22222" ALink="#B22222">

<center>
<a href="/docs/research/index.html">
<IMG width=216 height=28  SRC="/docs/images/tisr.gif" border=0 ALT="TIS Research"></A>
<HR  size=2 >
<img src="/docs/images/dms.gif">
<HR  size=2 >
</center>
<!-- Main Body -->

<Font size= 6>TIS/DMS Firewall Plus</font>
</p>
<blockquote>

<b>Overview</b></p> 

The TIS/DMS Firewall Plus is a Fortezza-enabled X.400 mail
guard/firewall. It has been designed to process and filter DMS-compliant
X.400 messages between two distinct network enclaves, based upon a
traffic flow configuration database.  This system is designed to be
flexible enough to allow the site administrator to configure X.400
message traffic filtering at varying degrees of granularity.  The
granularity of message filtering can be such that it restricts all, any,
or some message traffic between two networking enclaves.<p> 

<center>
<IMG SRC="/docs/images/dmspic.gif">
</Center>

<b>Flexibility</b><p>

The TIS/DMS Firewall Plus architecture is easily integrated to a
multilevel security (MLS) environment.  Currently, the TIS/DMS Firewall
Plus is not approved for use in a classified environment.  If ported to
an MLS system, the TIS/DMS Firewall Plus could be accredited for use as
a classified e-mail component. It could also be used as an integral part
of a complete firewall system, which makes the TIS/Firewall Plus a
versatile product.<p> 

<b>Architecture</b><p>

The TIS/DMS Firewall Plus system is supported by six main software
components: the HP-UX 10.01 operating system, the TIS Gauntlet Internet
Firewall, the X.400 Mail proxy,  the Nexor Messageware Message Transfer
Agent, the DMS Firewall Plus message filter dispatcher, and the DMS
Firewall Plus Administrator. Each of these components serve an important
function within the DMS Firewall Plus system. HP-UX 10.01 operating
system provides a stable base on which all of the other DMS Firewall
Plus system components can operate and interoperate efficiently. The
HP-UX operating system was chosen based on its reliability, stability,
and interoperability with the other DMS Firewall Plus COTS software
products making it a perfect foundation on which to build the DMS
Firewall Plus system.<p>

The TIS Gauntlet Internet Firewall provides a high level of network
security for the DMS Firewall Plus system. The DMS Firewall Plus
Gauntlet component has been configured with kernel network security
features, enabling only X.400 network traffic destined for the DMS
Firewall Plus to be accepted.  Additionally, the other network services,
such as, telnet, file transfer protocol, and remote execution services
have been removed, guaranteeing that only X.400 network traffic is
accepted and allowed to pass through the firewall.<p>

The X.400 Mail proxy component is configured to control the flow of
X.400 traffic between the two distinct network enclaves.  This proxy
utilizes the TIS Gauntlet Internet Firewall toolkit and network services
database to restrict the flow of X.400 traffic through the DMS Firewall
Plus system.<p>

The Nexor Messageware Message Transfer Agent is an X.400 UNIX-based
message server. It's main purpose within the DMS Firewall Plus is to
correctly interoperate with DMS-Compliant Message Transfer Agents to
which it is communicating.  The Nexor Messageware Message Transfer Agent
was chosen for use in the DMS Firewall Plus system because it conforms
to X.400 1988 and P1 standards.  This product also supports RFC 1006
allowing ISO traffic to be transmitted efficiently on the TCP/IP
network.<p>

The TIS/DMS Firewall Plus message filter dispatcher component is
primarily responsible for the processing of every incoming and outgoing
X.400 electronic mail message.  The purpose of the filter dispatcher is
to verify that all incoming and outgoing X.400 mail messages match the
exact filter requirements as specified by the traffic flow configuration
database.<p>


<center>
<IMG width=318 height=307 SRC="/docs/images/dmsarch2.gif"><br>
<font size=1>TIS/DMS Firewall Plus Architecture<p></font>
</Center>

The TIS/DMS Firewall Plus Administrator provides a user friendly
interface which can be used to easily configure the TIS/DMS Firewall
Plus to meet a specific site security policy.<p>
<HR>
<i>For more information, please contact:</I><P>
<B>Ralph Puga</b><BR>
(301)854-5323<br>
email:<a href="mailto:tis@tis.com">tis@tis.com<P>

</blockquote>

