<HEAD><TITLE>Trusted Mach Specifications</TITLE></HEAD>
<!--design & illustrations copyright 1996 Trusted Information Systems -->

<body bgcolor="#FFFFFF" text="#000000" Link="#191970" VLink="#B22222"
ALink="#B22222">

<center>
<a href="/docs/research/tmach/index.html">
<IMG width=117 height=51
SRC="/docs/images/tmach33.gif" border=0
ALT="TMACH"></A>
<HR  size=2 >
<IMG width=67 height=16
SRC="/docs/images/overview.gif" border=0
ALT="overview">
</center>
<HR  size=2 >

<!-- Top-->

<font size =6>Trusted Mach - Specifications</font>

<BLOCKQUOTE>

<B>Description:</b> <BR>
The Trusted Mach (TMach&reg;) system is a trusted
 software environment that intended as a base for well-known operating
system (O/S) interfaces (e.g., UNIX&reg;. NT&reg;). Targeted at the U.S.
security evaluation level of B3 (and an international F-B3/E5 rating), the TMach 
system satisfies both government and commercial information security requirements.
Highly portable, the TMach system can run on a wide array of hardware. Version 0.3b is
a Beta release of the evolving TMach system that provides the framework of
the TMach system. This version is available for distribution to interested parties
for the purpose of understanding the TMach system and performing early
application integration.
<P>

<B>Features:</B> <BR>
Version 0.3b of the TMach system provides the following:
<ul>
<li>          TMach Trusted Computing Base
<li>          POSIX Personality
<li>          Multiple Single Level Sessions
<li>          Single Level X Windows (X11R6)
<li>          Single Level Networking
<li>          TMach Software Development Kit
<li>          TMach User Documentation
<li>          TMach Interface Documentation
<li>          POSIX Documentation
</ul>
<p>

<b>Hardware:</b> <BR>
 Version 0.3b requires the following hardware:
<ul>
<li>          PC-AT based computer
<li>          INTEL 486 or INTEL Pentium processor<br>
			 (90Mhz or better recommended)
<li>          32 MB of main memory
<li>          one 1.44 MB 3.5" floppy disk drive
<li>          SCSI disk drive, 1 GB minimum for full installation, including:
<UL><li>			TMach Trusted Computing Base
<LI>	  			POSIX Personality
<LI>	 			 X Windows
<li>			TMach Software Development Kit
</ul>
<li>          Adaptec 1540/1542 series SCSI controller
<li>          Standard VGA video controller, or <br>
              Nitro 64 video controller<br>
              (or other Cirrus 5434 compatible video controller)
<li>		VGA color monitor
<li>		4mm DAT SCSI tape drive (required for installation)
</ul>
<p>

<b>Additional Supported Hardware:</b>
<ul>
<li>          up to 64 MB of main memory
<li>          a single disk drive up to 2 GB
<li>          one additional floppy disk drive, either 3.5" or 5.25"
<li>          two serial ports
<li>	      serial mouse
<li>	      two SMC Ether-EZ ethernet adapters
<li>	      HP 4M Plus serial printer
</ul>
<p>
<b>Cost:</b><br>
Version 0.3b of the TMach system is available worldwide. The price for US
customers is $500.00.<p>

<b>Installation Media:</b> <BR>
Version 0.3b of the TMach system is provided on three 3.5" floppy disks and three 4mm DAT cartridges.<p>

<b>Documentation:</b> <BR>
 The Installation Guide and related documents are
provided in printed form.  All documentation is provided in postscript
form on the system tapes.<p>

<b>Technical Support:</B>  <BR>
Requests for technical support on installing
Trusted Mach will be provided via telephone, 301-854-5716, or
e-mail: <A HREF="mailto:tmach-support@tis.com">tmach-support@tis.com</A>.
Integration and development support or consulting can be contracted from TIS.
<p>

<b>Training:</b>  <BR>
As we begin releasing the production version of the system, we
will provide TMach training courses. In the meantime, we will be happy to work
with beta customers to provide appropriate training on a case-by-case basis.
Call to discuss your training needs.  <p>

<b>Additional Information:</b>  <BR>
For additional information on
the TMach system, contact TIS at 301-854-5716, or send e-mail to
<A HREF="mailto:tmach-info@tis.com ">tmach-info@tis.com</A>. For business
arrangements or to receive information on other TIS products and
services, send E-mail to
<A HREF="mailto:tis@tis.com ">tis@tis.com</A> 
or write to:  Trusted Information Systems, Inc.,
3060 Washington Road (Route 97), Glenwood, Maryland 21738.
<P>

Price and conditions subject to change without notice.
