<html>
<head>
   <title>Functional Summary - 9. Product Testing Methodology</title>
<!-- Copyright 1996 Trusted Information Systems -->
<!-- Design and programming: The James Gang (jgang@jamesgang.com) -->
</HEAD>

<BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF" text="#000000" Link="#191970" VLink="#B22222" ALink="#B22222">

<center>
<a href="/docs/products/gauntlet/index.html">
<IMG width=284 height=65  SRC="/docs/images/gtop.gif" border=0 ALT="gauntlet"></A>
<HR  size=2 >
<IMG width=135 height=16  SRC="/docs/images/funct.gif" border=0 ALT="functional summary">
</center>
<HR  size=2 >
<!-- Main Body -->

<Font size= 6<A NAME="9">9. Product testing methodology
</a></font>
<BLOCKQUote>


<P>
The Gauntlet Internet Firewall development team and quality assurance
group, test new implementations of the product, going through
the following steps:
<UL>
<LI>Assurance review of protocol before implementation
<LI>Design check of new features against Gauntlet Design Criteria
<LI>Review of code changes and new service support by Quality
Assurance group and Gauntlet Principal Engineer and Architect
<LI>Development of test plan, to include regression testing and
comprehensive testing of all features and services
<LI>Internal testing of software base levels in test lab
<LI>External testing of software by resellers and field test customers
<LI>Second external test of  software
</UL>

<P>
Outside reviewers often review our software. 
<P>
Also, the Gauntlet Internet Firewall development team and QA group
use independently developed &quot;Internet Attack&quot; tools
against new versions of the product, and new features.
</BLOCKQUote>

