<head>
   <title>Functional Summary - 11. Product Operational Assumptions</title>


<!-- Copyright 1996 Trusted Information Systems -->
<!-- Design and programming: The James Gang (jgang@jamesgang.com) -->
</HEAD>

<BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF" text="#000000" Link="#191970" VLink="#B22222" ALink="#B22222">

<center>
<a href="/docs/products/gauntlet/index.html">
<IMG width=284 height=65  SRC="/docs/images/gtop.gif" border=0 ALT="gauntlet"></A>
<HR  size=2 >
<IMG width=135 height=16  SRC="/docs/images/funct.gif" border=0 ALT="functional summary">
</center>
<HR  size=2 >
<!--Main Body -->

<Font size= 6><A NAME="11">11. Product operational assumptions
</a></font>
<BLOCKQUote>


<P>
The Gauntlet Internet Firewall is designed to work as a gateway
between IP networks. The standard hardware configuration from
Trusted Information Systems, Inc., comes with dual Ethernet devices.
Other network hardware can be used with our Gauntlet Firewall
Software products, as long as the base operating system supports
them. Contact TIS or your Gauntlet Authorized Reseller for specific
device information.
<P>
No other operational assumptions are made.
</BLOCKQUote>
