<HTML>
<HEAD><TITLE>Transparent Firewalls</TITLE>

<!-- Copyright 1996 Trusted Information Systems -->
<!-- Design and programming: The James Gang (jgang@jamesgang.com) -->
</HEAD>

<BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF" text="#000000" Link="#191970" VLink="#B22222"
ALink="#B22222">

<center>
<a href="/docs/products/gauntlet/index.html">
<IMG width=284 height=65
SRC="/docs/images/gtop.gif" border=0
ALT="gauntlet"></A>
<HR  size=2 >
<IMG width=67 height=16
SRC="/docs/images/overview.gif" border=0
ALT="overview">
</center>
<HR  size=2 >

<!-- Main Body -->

<Font size= 6>Transparent Firewalls for Internet and Intranet
Applications</font>
<P><center>
<IMG width=216 height=51
SRC="/docs/images/transpar.gif" border=0
ALT="transparent gauntlet illustration"></center>
<Blockquote>
Gauntlet Internet Firewalls let you extend your organization's network
security by establishing a Virtual Network Perimeter. Remote offices can
network with your main office with the <a
href="/docs/products/gauntlet/gauntlet6.html">Gauntlet Net Extender</A>. The Gauntlet PC Extender allows traveling users with
remote access
to become a part of your trusted network. And the Gauntlet
Intranet Firewall allows controlled access between trusted workgroups inside
your organization.
<BR>
<BR>

<Font size = 4><B>Gauntlet Internet Firewall</B> </font>
<BR>

Gauntlet Internet Firewalls provide the transparency and ease-of-operation
of filtering router firewalls, but our application-level security services
strongly regulate both incoming and outgoing communications. Our proxy-based
system passes only application data, so security is assured. Gauntlet Internet
Firewalls look like they are behaving as an internetwork router, but supply
proxy-based security for specific provided services. Gauntlet updates include
additional proxies as additional services are developed.
<BR><Center>
<IMG width=360 height=143
SRC="/docs/images/internet.gif" border=0
ALT="Gauntlet - Internet"></center>
<BR>
Gauntlet Internet Firewalls also allow multi-national companies to build
<a
href="/docs/products/gauntlet/gauntlet5.html">Global Virtual Private Networks</a> (GVPNs) over low cost Internet communications links. Our
<a
href="/docs/products/gauntlet/gauntlet5.html">Commercial Key Escrow</a> (CKE) system allows corporations to utilize their own
data recovery centers. Other services available on Gauntlet Internet
Firewalls include Domain Name Service (DNS), a secure Web server, secure Anonymous FTP, and <a
href="/docs/products/gauntlet/gauntlet5.html">Internet
electronic mail</a>. Gauntlet Firewalls are IPSEC-ready,
X.400/X.500 compatible, NSA MISSI approved, and DoD DMS compliant.
<BR>
<BR>


<Font size = 4><B>Gauntlet Intranet Firewall </B></font>
<BR>

As a manager, you're always searching for ways to maximize speed and
productivity using the resources you already have. As an add-on feature
to your existing Gauntlet Internet Firewall, a Gauntlet Intranet Firewall
allows you to place additional network strongholds within your security
perimeter. You can pass authorized information quickly and securely inside
your organization. It can be easily managed locally or remotely, using
the same access rules and features provided by your Gauntlet Internet Firewall.
<BR>
<center>
<IMG width=258 height=252
SRC="/docs/images/intranet.gif" border=0
ALT="Gauntlet - Intranet"></center>
<BR>
For management, Gauntlet Firewalls also include:

<ul>
<li>	 A secure, graphical management interface, accessible from an authorized computer on your trusted network. </li>

<li>	 A firewall system integrity checker using cryptographic checksums
to detect and report any changes in the system software. </li>

<li>&quot;Smoke alarms&quot; that can be configured to &quot;go off&quot;
any time connections to unsupported services are attempted. </li>

<li>	 An audit tool that provides audit reduction and reporting on a timely
basis. </li>
</ul>

</Blockquote>

<a href="/docs/products/gauntlet/gauntlet5.html">
