<HTML>
<HEAD><TITLE>The need for a firewall</TITLE>

<!-- Copyright 1996 Trusted Information Systems -->
<!-- Design and programming: The James Gang (jgang@jamesgang.com) -->
</HEAD>

<BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF" text="#000000" Link="#191970" VLink="#B22222"
ALink="#B22222">

<center>
<a href="/docs/products/gauntlet/index.html">
<IMG width=284 height=65
SRC="/docs/images/gtop.gif" border=0
ALT="gauntlet"></A>
<HR  size=2 >
<IMG width=67 height=16
SRC="/docs/images/overview.gif" border=0
ALT="overview">
</center>
<HR  size=2 >

<!-- Main Body -->

<Font size= 6>Key Technical Features: <BR>
VPN, E-mail and Encryption</font>
<Blockquote>


<Font size = 4><B>Virtual Private Network</B></Font>
<BR>
Virtual Private Networks (VPNs) allow privacy
for all allowed network traffic between two Gauntlet Firewall-protected
gateways through the Data Encryption Standard. No level of trust between
networks is assumed. But when a trusted relationship exists between networks,
the security perimeters may be extended. Users can economically establish
security-assured, high-speed, Internet VPNs at a fraction of the operating
expense of dedicated, leased-line networks. Gauntlet Internet Firewalls
come standard with software encryption; hardware encryption and Commercial
Key Recovery are available.
<p>
<Font size = 4><B>Electronic Mail</B></Font>
<BR>
Electronic Mail Gauntlet Firewalls act as a mail gateway for Internet
standard SMTP mail, employing a small, secure SMTP proxy. This process
runs as an SMTP server on the Gauntlet Internet Firewall and gathers incoming
mail. Our system hides internal e-mail addresses from the outside, and
can be configured to act as a POP3 access point for external users to gain
access to their mail.
<BR>
<BR>
<Font size= 4><B>Escrow Enabled Gauntlet Internet Firewall</B></font>
<BR>
The Escrow Enabled Gauntlet Internet Firewall incorporates TIS's RecoverKey&#153; technology to support recovery of the content of encrypted
communications between Gauntlet Internet Firewalls. For users who are concerned
about the abuse of their Virtual Private Networks, RecoverKey technology offers
the capability of monitoring encrypted traffic from a company-controlled
Key Recovery Center (KRC).
<BR>
<BR>
In addition, international Gauntlet Internet Firewall customers who
want the benefits of full 56-bit DES encryption for their VPNs can have
those benefits worldwide by using the Escrow Enabled Gauntlet Internet Firewall.

</Blockquote><BR>



