<HTML>
<HEAD><TITLE>Firewall Support</TITLE>

<!-- Copyright 1996 Trusted Information Systems -->
<!-- Design and programming: The James Gang (jgang@jamesgang.com) -->
</HEAD>

<BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF" text="#000000" Link="#191970" VLink="#B22222"
ALink="#B22222">

<center>
<a href="/docs/products/gauntlet/index.html">
<IMG width=284 height=65
SRC="/docs/images/gtop.gif" border=0
ALT="gauntlet"></A>
<HR  size=2 >
<IMG width=67 height=16
SRC="/docs/images/overview.gif" border=0
ALT="overview">
</center>
<HR  size=2 >

<!-- Main Body -->
<Font size= 6>Expert Security Consulting</font>
<P>
<center>
<IMG width=172 height=170
SRC="/docs/images/slide2.gif" border=0 ALT="demo"
>
</center>
<Blockquote>
Gauntlet Internet Firewalls feature software originally based on Trusted
Information Systems' popular Internet Firewall Toolkit -- the de facto Internet
standard for application gateway firewalls now in use at over 15,000 sites
on six continents. For over a decade, TIS has been the world's leading
computer, communications and network security research, development and
consulting firm. TIS is a charter member of both the Firewall Product Developers
Consortium and the S/WAN Initiative. No other firewall provider can offer
our level of security knowledge or customer support.
<BR>
<BR>
To maintain the security of your business' vital operations, TIS offers
optional technical support, on-site installation and training, and upgrades.
Telephone support is available. You can also receive our periodic upgrades,
giving you the most current services and proxies available. You get full
product support through TIS's research, integration, development and consulting
services.

</Blockquote>
<center>
<IMG width=275 height=190
SRC="/docs/images/phonesupport.gif" border=0
ALT="phone support" >
</center>
<p>
<a href="/docs/products/gauntlet/index.html">
<IMG width=60 height=24
SRC="/docs/images/next.gif" border=0 ALT="next">
Gauntlet Main Menu</a>


<!-- Menu -->

<Center>
<Blockquote>
<HR  size=4 >

<FORM METHOD="GET" ACTION="/docs/cgi-bin/AnyURL.cgi">
<select name="level">

<option
