<a name="FSPM">
[FSPM] Triad Formal Security Policy Model, TIS report #0490, CDRL #A011,
July, 1994.
<p>

<a name="Reyn89">
[Reyn89] Franklin D. Reynolds, et al, ``Draft Alpha Release-2 Kernel
Interface Specification,'' 17 Jan 1989.
<p>

<a name="Spiv">
[Spiv] J.M. Spivey, The Z Notation: A Reference Manual, Prentice
Hall International, 1989.
<p>

<a name="SCC">
[SCC] Secure Computing Corporation, ``Formal Security Policy Model
for Distributed Trusted Mach,'' Rome Laboratory Contract No. F30602-91-C-0136.
<p>

<a name="Sterne">
[Sterne] Daniel F. Sterne, ``On the Buzzword `Security Policy',''
1991 IEEE Symposium on Research in Security and Privacy, Oakland, Calif.
<p>

<a name="TMM">
[TMM] Trusted Information Systems, ``A Mathematical Model of
TMach,'' December, 1993.
<p>

<a name="IDD">
[IDD] Triad Interface Design Document, TIS report #0602,
CDRL#A014, 14 June  1996.
<p>

<a name="TMachPoP">
[TMachPoP] Trusted Mach, Philosophy of Protection
Document No: TIS TMACH Edoc-003-93B,  21 May 1993.
<p>

<a name="Benzel">
[Benzel] Terry C. Vickers Benzel, E. John Sebes, Homayoon Tajalli,
``Identificatiion of Subjects and Objects in a Trusted Extensible
Client Server Architecture'', Trusted Information Systems, Inc., 18th
National Information Systems Security Conference October 10-13, 1995,
Baltimore, MD.
<p>

Technical society and technical association
specifications and standards are generally available for reference
from libraries.  They are also distributed among technical groups and
using Federal Agencies.<P>
