<!-- Main Body -->
<FONT SIZE=6>Philosophy of Protection for Triad</FONT>
<BLOCKQUOTE>
<h2>
Notes
</h2>
This section lists the acronyms used in this document.
<P>
<HR>
<table cellpadding = 0>
<TR> <TD> ACL     <TD> Access Control List </TD>
<TR> <TD> AIS     <TD> Automated Information-processing System </TD>
<TR> <TD> BLP     <TD> Bell-LaPadula </TD>
<TR> <TD> DAC     <TD> Discretionary Access Control </TD>
<TR> <TD> DoD     <TD> Department of Defense </TD>
<TR> <TD> FS      <TD> File Server </TD>
<TR> <TD> FSPM    <TD> Formal Security Policy Model </TD>
<TR> <TD> IPC     <TD> Inter-Process Communication </TD>
<TR> <TD> ITSEC   <TD> Information Technology Security Evaluation Criteria </TD>
<TR> <TD> OOL     <TD> Out-Of-Line </TD>
<TR> <TD> ORA     <TD> Odyssey Research Associates </TD>
<TR> <TD> PoP     <TD> Philosophy of Protection </TD>
<TR> <TD> RMO     <TD> Real Memory Object </TD>
<TR> <TD> RNS     <TD> Root Name Server </TD>
<TR> <TD> RPC     <TD> Remote Procedure Call </TD>
<TR> <TD> RVM     <TD> Reference Validation Mechanism </TD>
<TR> <TD> SAK     <TD> Secure Attention Key </TD>
<TR> <TD> TASH    <TD> Trusted Administration Shell </TD>
<TR> <TD> TCB     <TD> Trusted Computing Base </TD>
<TR> <TD> TCSEC   <TD> Trusted System Security Evaluation Criteria </TD>
<TR> <TD> TSH     <TD> Trusted Shell </TD>
</table><P>
