<!-- Main Body -->
<P>

<Font size= 6>Philosophy of Protection for Triad</font>
<BLOCKQUOTE>
<h2>
Trusted Subjects
</h2>

<h2>
</h2>

Triad has no trusted subjects.
Although trusted server tasks are active entities, they are not
trusted subjects because they are part of the TCB.
It is the TCB that uses privileged kernel services to create subjects,
as described in the section on <a href="serv.html#Sserversubject">Subjects</a>.
Each subject consists of single-level tasks with no kernel privileges,
and hence subjects are not trusted.
<P><P>

<a href="/docs/research/distributed/verif.html">
<IMG width=60 height=24
SRC="/docs/images/next.gif" border=0
ALT="next"> Verification Plan</a>


