<HTML>
<HEAD><TITLE>Advanced Joint Planning
- Advanced Concept Technology Demonstration </title>
<!-- Copyright 1996 Trusted Information Systems -->
<!-- Design and programming: The James Gang (jgang@jamesgang.com) -->
</HEAD>

<body bgcolor="#FFFFFF" text="#000000" Link="#191970" VLink="#B22222" ALink="#B22222">

<center>
<a href="/docs/products/consulting/index.html">
<IMG width=230 height=33  SRC="/docs/images/tisc.gif" border=0 ALT="TIS Consulting"></A>
<HR  size=2 >
<IMG width=172 height=16 SRC="/docs/images/govtcon.gif" border=0 ALT="Government Consulting">
</center>

<HR  size=2 >

<!-- Main Body -->

<Font size= 4>Support for Operational Commanders<br>
Advanced Joint Planning
- Advanced Concept Technology Demonstration </font>
<BLOCKQUOTE>
TIS is providing security engineering support for the Advanced Joint Planning
(AJP) - Advanced Concept Technology Demonstration (ACTD).  These
technologies ultimately will be transitioned into the Global Command
and Control System (GCCS) Leading Edge Services (LES)
<P>
The AJP-ACTD rapidly inserts supportable 
technology to meet the Regional Commander-in-Chief's (CINC's) 
immediate command and control requirements. The overall goal of 
the AJP-ACTD is to develop, demonstrate, harden and leave in 
place an enhanced C4I operational capability tailored to the 
operational concepts of a theater CINC. Accelerated and collaborative 
operations will be possible throughout the command and control 
structure by hardening advanced command and control tools with 
the applicable concepts of operations. The process for 
evolutionary development and acquisition of mission critical 
command and control systems will be re-engineered by 
emphasizing close interaction between developers and users. 
Integrated systems and support processes developed by this 
program will transition to the Global Command and Control 
System (GCCS) Leading Edge System (LES). The AJP-ACTD will 
leave behind a workable capability for the operator. 
<P>
The intent of the AJP-ACTD is to produce a framework which 
is readily upgraded and expanded to include emgerging C4I 
and planning technologies. Some of the emerging technologies 
targeted for inclusion are the 
<a href="/docs/products/consulting/govt/jtf.html">JTF ATD</A>
program, the Defense 
Modeling and Simulation Office's (DMSO) COMPASS initiative, which 
focuses on improving joint mission planning capabilities, and 
several ARPA technology initiatives that may provide new 
capabilities for intelligent systems, advanced information 
processing, expert systems and distributed systems. 
<P>
The AJP-ACTD is part of an integrated testing and development
environment known as the Virtual Testbed (VTB). The VTB's purpose is 
to facilitate rapid transition of advanced technology into operational
use, and consists of different layers of activities: Research and
Development, ATDs, ACTDs, and GCCS LES. Ultimately, the new
successful technologies will be integrated into the operational GCCS. 
The VTB consists of a variety of networks, software infrastructures,
applications, procedures, and support which contribute to the 
complexity and range of security implications and issues.<P>
<P>
TIS's efforts will focus on providing ongoing security engineering, 
and certification and accreditation support to NRaD for the 
AJP-ACTD program. These include developing security documents 
for the AJP-ACTD such as the Security Concept 
of Operations (CONOPS), the System Security Plan, and the System 
Security Requirements.  These security documents are tailored 
to the AJP-ACTD operational environment at USACOM in Norfolk, 
VA. They will be used in the certification and accreditation 
process of the system at that site. 
<P>
In addition, support efforts will also include analyses of how 
these efforts relate to applications in other command/theater 
environments, emerging and evolving security requirements, 
and new security products. 
<P>
<HR>
<H3>Additional Information</H3>
<P>
<ul>
<li><a href="nrad10.html">The AJP-ACTD DARPA/ITO Project Summary</A><br>
<LI><a href="http://www.darpa.mil/ajp_actd/">DARPA AJP-ACTD Home Page<BR>
</UL>
