<BLOCKQUOTE>
<p>
<h3>II.  Vendor Claims</h3><p>
<CENTER>
<TABLE border=2 cellpadding=4>
<TR>
<TD><b>Vendor Claim/Important Consideration</B></TD>
<TD><B>Validated</B></TD>            
<TD><B>Comments</B></TD>
</TR>

<TR>
<TD>IP forwarding disabled</TD>
<TD>Validated</TD>                     
<TD>None</TD>
</TR>

<TR>
<TD>No direct login to the firewall (other than the console)</TD>
<TD>Validated</TD>                    
<TD>This is configurable through the configuration menus (gauntlet-admin)</TD>
</TR>

<TR>
<TD>Direct login attempts to the firewall are audited</TD>
<TD>Validated</TD>                    
<TD>in /var/log/messages file<br>
Unlimited login attempts are permitted<br>
Valid user names are recorded</TD>
</TR>

<TR>
<TD>Telnet and FTP from external networks require strong authentication</TD>
<TD>Validated</TD>                     
<TD>This is configurable from the netperm table</TD>
</TR>

<TR>
<TD>Appropriate permission set on the file system<br>
- any unnecessary programs with SUID/SGID permissions</TD>
<TD> </TD>                       
<TD>limited testing - more study needed on a few files:<br>
/usr/bin/rdist and /usr/sbin/restore<br>
COPS auditing tool not run against the Gauntlet configuration</TD>
</TR>

<TR>
<TD>Only necessary programs are installed<br>
-programming tools removed<br>
-dangerous services disabled</TD>
<TD>Validated</TD> 
<TD>limited testing -</TD>
</TR>


<TR>
<TD>The syslogd has been replaced to enhance security</TD>
<TD>Not Validated</TD>                      
<TD>Syslogd appears not to have been patched with the BSDI patch 
(CERT advisory:October 19, 1995<br>
NOTE: Gauntlet firewall configurations supplied after October 19, 1995 
have been equipped with the proper patch.</TD>
</TR>

<TR>
<TD>All outgoing proxies are transparent<br>
-ftp<br>
-telnet<br>
-http/gopher<br>
-rlogin<br>
-xwindows</TD>
<TD>Validated<br>
Validated<br>
Validated<br>
Validated<br></TD>                        
<TD>Proxy transparency can be configured from the netperm table<p>
X-windows not tested</TD>
</TR>

<TR>
<TD>No RPC services available</TD>
<TD>Validated</TD>                     
<TD>rpcinfo -p bob<br>
Gauntlet responds:<br>
security alert[IP address of sender]<br>
rpcinfo: can't contact portmapper:<br>
RPC:remote system error - connection refused
 </TD>
</TR>

<TR>
<TD>The following tools come with the Gauntlet Firewall<br>
-software for installing binary upgrades<br>
-software for checking digital signatures of system files<br>
-tools for audit log reduction and reporting<br>
-system alert and trouble monitoring
</TD>
<TD><P>Validated<p>
Validated<p>
Validated<p>
Validated</TD>                   
<TD>The testing validated the presence of these tools in the 
Gauntlet firewall. The tools themselves were not tested by the team.</TD>
</TR>

<TR>
<TD>system retains one week of logs automatically in var.log</TD>
<TD>Validated</TD>                     
<TD>
 </TD>
</TR>

<TR>
<TD>second set of logs retained in compressed format files</TD>
<TD>Validated</TD>                     
<TD>
 </TD>
</TR>

<TR>
<TD>active system log is under /var/system/messages</TD>
<TD>Validated</TD>                     
<TD>
 </TD>
</TR>

<TR>
<TD>system defines a list of events NOT noteworthy...all other occurences
are brought to the system admins attention
</TD>
<TD>Validated</TD>                     
<TD>Located in file called /usr/local/etc/frequentcheck.ignore
 </TD>
</TR>

<TR>
<TD>system maintains an online checksum database</TD>
<TD>Validated</TD>                     
<TD>database is located in /usr/local/etc/checksums
 </TD>
</TR>

<TR>
<TD>system integrity check picks up changes to system files</TD>
<TD>Validated</TD>                     
<TD>Results of integrity checks against changed files:<br>
1.)/etc/passwd change:<br>
/etc/passwd: checksum does not match any recorded value<br>
2.)/etc/passwd add non root, UID 0 user:<br>
/etc/passwd: checksum does not match any recorded value<br>
3.)add no passwd user:<br>
/etc/passwd: checksum does not match any recorded value<br>
4.)/ make world writable:<br>
/; mode changed 040755->040777<br>
5.).rhosts make world writable:<br>
/root/.rhosts; mode changed 012755->012777<br>
6.).profile change:<br>
/.profile:checksum does not match any recorded value<br>
7.) /bin/sh change:<br>
/bin/sh: checksum does not match any recorded value<br>
</TD>
</TR>

<TR>
<TD>system integrity check picks up addition of files to the filesystem</TD>
<TD>Validated</TD>                     
<TD>add a file to the filesystem:<br>
/filename:newfile
 </TD>
</TR>

<TR>
<TD>audit log keeps records of all outgoing http requests</TD>
<TD>Validated</TD>                     
<TD>Audit logs for https include the URL requested
 </TD>
</TR>

<TR>
<TD>the ftp proxy can be configured down to the specific command</TD>
<TD>Not Tested</TD>                     
<TD>according to the user's guide the ftp proxy can be configured so that 
auth is required for certain ftp commands only - this capability was <b>not</b>
tested by the test team
 </TD>
</TR>

<TR>
<TD>the http proxy provide access control on the servers being accessed</TD>
<TD>Validated</TD>                     
<TD>admin is able to deny access to certain web servers based on IP address
 </TD>
</TR>

<TR>
<TD>all authentication database updates to the gauntlet are logged</TD>
<TD>Validated</TD>                     
<TD>/usr/var/log/messages
 </TD>
</TR>

</TABLE>
</CENTER>


