You have mail.<p>

badguy%<p>

<p>

	<i>Expected Result</i>:  If this test is successful, the command prompt 
(badguy%) should appear on hq.peaceful.mil, the computer initiating the 
telnet session.<p>

<p>

	<i>Observed Result</i>:  This test showed that the telnet proxy operates 
as expected from an inside machine to an outside machine through the firewall.<p>

<p>

<p>

	<i>Test #3</i>:  Telnet from hq.peaceful.mil to badguy.attack.mil through 
gauntlet.peaceful.mil (the Gauntlet firewall) using transparency.<p>

<p>

	<i>Purpose</i>:  To verify that the Telnet protocol works as expected 
on the firewall.  The user should not have to do a telnet to the firewall 
before doing a telnet to the target machine because transparency is enabled 
on the firewall.<p>

<p>

	<I>Procedures:</i><p>

