Trying euser1@222.222.222.2 ...<p>

Password:<p>

Last login: Wed Jan 24 15:37:30 from gauntlet.peaceful.mil<p>

Sun Microsystems Inc.   SunOS  5.4  Generic July 1994<p>

You have mail.<p>

badguy%<p>

<p>

	<i>Expected Results</i>:  If successful, the command prompt (badguy%) 
should appear on hq.peaceful.mil, the computer initiating the rlogin session.<p>

<p>

	<i>Observed Result</i>:  Rlogin session initiation from hq.peaceful.mil 
to badguy.attack.mil through gauntlet.peaceful.mil without transparency 
was successful.<p>

<p>

<p>

	<i>Test #3</i>:  Rlogin from hq.peaceful.mil to badguy.attack.mil 
through gauntlet.peaceful.mil (the Gauntlet firewall) using transparency.<p>

<p>

	<i>Purpose</i>:  To verify that the rlogin protocol works as 
expected on the firewall.  The user should not have to do an rlogin 
into the firewall before doing an rlogin into the target machine.<p>

<p>

	<i>Procedures</i>:<p>

hq% <b>rlogin -l euser1 badguy.attack.mil</b><p>

Trying euser1@222.222.22.2 ...<p>

